title: Comfortably Numb
author: maleeha
text: two paths,  both deceiving in their own separate ways.  she knows choices cannot be undone engraved in stone,   her decisions are always there,  never gone.  like sand stuck in her sandals.  like a daunting whisper in the back of her mind,  always reminding.   it comes in waves,  every now and again.  but they aren't gentle waves,  not the rhythmical crash of the blue tones on earthy shores.  an excruciatingly coarse wind pushing against her bony frame,  a cuttingly bitter rush of water bleeding into her thoughts.    it leaves scars,  so many along her body.  she feels exposed,  raw,  tender,  like there is nothing there covering her bones,  and her wounds are open to the violent,  salty winds.  yet no one takes notice because her scars are invisible to the rest.   there are people who try to understand her,  try to help her.  but she needs to let go of their helping hand,  face her problems alone.  just like she always has.   when she observes the blooming flowers outside,  nothing but emptiness fills her soul.  when the rain she used to love to watch comes pouring down,   all she thinks of is how a cloud of her misfortune and regret has come crashing down,  falling upon her skin,  scalding and singeing.    people say that rain stops,  eventually.  that the pain stops,  the heartache,  the grief,  the regret,  the sorrow,  the unhappiness.  but she no longer has that one thing,  that one thing that can provide a shred of humanity.   hope.    she says it has ceased to exist in her mind.  yet i fail to believe this,  because as i watch her struggle and battle,  she knows she has a purpose,  ambition.  she accepts the fact that there is no other way to escape the endless horizons of solitude,  other than to fill her mind with heartwarming memories that act as medicine.   she must remind herself of the blooming fragrances of delicate petals she tended to so tenderly,  out in the backyard,  now all wilted and withered away,  longing for her touch.  she must remind herself of the astounding hues blending together and reflecting off the blackening waves,   pulling her away from her worries.  she must remind herself of the limitless and devoted love she shared with the young man who,  after all these years,  is still waiting,  never given up.   it will take time.  worthy,  meaningful time will be used to soothe her broken mind,  but she wonâ’t let it slide through her fingers.  persist and pursue she will.  because she has so much to live for,  so much opportunity,  a boundless book of choices and chances.   and maybe some years from now,  in some fantasy,   sheâ’ll be gardening her heart away in the backyard,  picking the roses with the most heavenly fragrances sheâ’ll be enjoying the music of the ocean,  the soft cries of the gulls.  she will have settled down with her soulmate,  who will never leave,  because he is me.   only time will tell.

title: The eight legged monster

text: the eight legged        monster   am i afraid? most certainly not bravery is what i got  i box,  i climb,  do stunts with my bike i fish hunt,  do impossible hikes  iâ’m strong and tough and never been scared  iâ’ve accepted almost every dare  but when it comes to the monster of eight my bravery is up for debate   iâ’ll jump off a cliff be a sky diver but iâ’ll never,  ever love spiders  when my friends say itâ’s smaller than you donâ’t be afraid i think to myself yeah so is a grenade  but then one day to my surprise  i saw that devil before my eyes  it doesnâ’t see me i donâ’t think  but then i saw the spider wink  it took one step i begin to quiver it took a couple more i begin to shiver  a million places for the intruder to hide i want this spider to go outside   this spider could hide all over the place i will not rest until i know iâ’m safe  this spider needs to go out i cannot have it running about  i feel like itâ’s staring into my soul  i wouldnâ’t touch it with a 10 foot pole   blow torch,  chainsaw,  my pocket knife iâ’ve never been more scared in my life  i make my choice i turn my head i wanted that spider to be dead  but then something occurred much to my fright i let that spider out of my sight  where is it i cannot speak?  this is giving me the creeps i feel on my back little hairs i scream for help but no ones there  iâ’ll take on bats,  snakes,  even a mouse but if i see a spider i might burn down my house  i run out of my room with fear from my head to toes i feel like its crawling on my nose  i check my blankets i checked my bed what is wrong with my head?  this isnâ’t me i am tough i fought through everything nice and rough   iâ’ll never admit i screamed like a lady iâ’ll never admit i may have been more scared than a baby  if anyone asks i will not tell iâ’ll say iâ’m brave and doing swell  iâ’ll take on robbers,  aliens,  and flying saucers  but i am deathly scared of that eight legged monster

title: Columbus Killed
author: maren
text: in 1492,  columbus sailed the ocean blue.    that rhyme you know,  that verse alone,    but here's some things you've never known;  in 1493,  columbus claimed all he could see.    he shouted out,  'it's for the king!''  everyone and everything!  in 1494,  columbus set the tone for war.    in 1495,  he said he'd leave few men alive.    by 1496,  and entire continent was sick.    by 1497,  most indians had left for heaven.   in 1498,  the king proclaimed,  'this man is great!''  i think it says a thing or two,   about the things we like to do,   that when we see a murderer this way,   we give him a national holiday.

title: Questions to the unknown
author: marina
text: i wonder what the unknown would perceive our pandemonius world to be  would they laugh in the conception of our laws,   or cry in the fear of our reliance drawn to them? when our eyes hit the surface of our unsteady handheld technology for hours at once,  would they distinguish the past,   or feel the surrounding presence of the future? in being violated of what we choose to place on our bodies to cover our figure,  would they too,  feel the self doubt of oneâ’s body yet change their exterior because inapposite boys won't amend their interior,   or do they too,  attempt to conceal their sacred form?  do they find it peculiar at the lack of respect towards diversity and difference that leads us to crowded repetitive roads filled with frantic screams and marches against society,   or do they know the solution?  do they relish the accessibility of transportation to explorations,   or judge the sudden crave to immigrate your fatherland? do they believe we entail adjustment?  will they open our human eyes? and if they won't,   will we ever learn to open them ourselves?

title: Too Young
author: marissa
text: too young  as i think back now i can remember the day so clearly.  pollutant rain mixed with salty tears.  did you not have a right to cry,  to mourn the loss of someone? the gravestone new,  hastily sketched words and letters that were unimportant.   too young.   seven,  such an age to experience such loss.  the worst parts,  the sympathetic looks.  words hung losely in the air,  clouding with doubt.  new feelings bubble inside the heart,  like kerosene dousing it,  one match,  just one thing to set them all,  was all that was needed.   much too young.   take advantage of the sympathetic looks.  everyone knows the feeling of loss,  leave you alone in these desperate times.  company was needed.  and yet it was unwanted.  you wanted them to mourn with you,  beside you,  for you,  and yet their looks sickened you.  what hypocritical world indeed.   always too young.   and two feelings scared you the most.  the feeling of apathy and the fear.  indifference was startiling,  why could you not feel.  it was a emotional tramatizing experince,  but maybe denial was stronger.  and the fear,  death kissed the air,  and reminded even the most optimistic that a demise was inevitable.  so was crying a mistake or a blessing from the shallow cage?  simply too young.   they pull you away,  friends and famalies of the dearly departed,  murmer,  even without your absence.  hypothermia was the least of concerns,  but there voices dragged you away from the serenity of thought,  to the reality that lays ahead.  forgivness isnt an easy thing to give,  especially not to yourself.   youth is taken,  easily so,  and replaced by maturity.  because they're always too young.  but the world is cruel,  and as a mother raised by the hand,  she shall do the same to you.

title: The Scream
author: mariya
text: a sound a noise a boom a shout a scream the world seemed to be coming to an end.  no one knew that the scream would occur.  it was an ordinary day.   suddenly  nature bubbled up.  the heat was unbearable.  the sight was remarkable.  nature spoke.  nature screamed.   the volcano shook violently.  heat began to rise.  air filled with smoke.  then,  for a second the world stayed still but not for  long.  the lava sprang into the blue sky and then it was blue no more.  sky,  red like the color of great burnet sun,  the color of pouteria caimito.  it was because of the scream of nature.   only the scream of nature could be heard only the smoke and the red sky could be seen.  chills on everyoneâ’s body.  worry in everyoneâ’s face.    nature did not scream often.   but when it did it made itself known it made itself heard  eruption explosion outbreak bang blast he ran the man who had seen it all the man who saw nature scream the man who never saw it before shock surprise fright distress hands covering ears he ran and never looked back for the scream of nature has impacted all.

title: All Hallow's Eve
author: marja
text: every year at a certain time,  children dress up,  be it a ghost,  a ghoul or mime.  but not only the children don a disguise,  to know who it is,  you'd be surprised.  for it is the trees who dress up in costume,  always bright colors,  never in sad gloom.  many bright colors,  red,  orange,  and yellow,  so much bright color,  it sure doesn't look sallow.  yet unlike children they don't trick-or-treat,  for trees as you know are quite without feet.

title: The Midnight Shore
author: mark
text: the smell of salt the sound of rain the chilling breeze  the crystal sand  the glowing moon  all present,  as i walk along the midnight shore   i walk along the crystal sand stalked by the horizon knowing so little of what to expect,  haunted by possibilities   the ocean howls gleaming in moonlight powerful and cold merciless and brave  silence… all is still except for the whispering waves crashing and crashing,  each time stronger than the last the rising tide,  creeping closer every night  calm and still or rough and mean a restless soul  the ocean sleeps  dark as obsidian,  toying with my soul illusive figures which i am never able to find  a bottomless pit,  as vast as can be more dangerous than oneâ’s wildest dreams adventurous sailors head out to the beach massive and small,  all will fall the hungry waves set out on their hunt once confident sailors,  now never to see the light of day  as i walk home i glance back once more the waves now gentle the ocean now peaceful,  inviting me back to the beautiful shore  yet i know this to be nothing  more than a trick a facade masking the true evil possessed by the starving waves each night,  creeping closer to their prey.

title: The Lone Wolf
author: mark
text: eyes like the ocean fur dark as coal coat soft as cotton claws of an eagle  roaming the chilling woods in search of her next feast though angry and panicked fearless and bold  the bushes rustle *silence* the bunny hops the wolf turns they lock eyes and the bunny knows,  the wolf has found its prey  she swipes her right paw once a ball of fluff now spattered with blood once a peaceful creature now a meal,  for the midnight wolf  she howls and howls all through the night for where did her pack go?  she wonders in fright still confused she cries all night  abandoned and hurt fierce and vicious a powerful beta now only a memory  beginning to adapt,  life as a lone wolf,  successfully hunting,  feasting away forgetting her old,  miserable ways continuing to prosper,   she learns along the way that she never needed the pack but rather,  the pack always needed her.

title: Making Waves
author: matt
text: water sprinted down the wash,  enjoying the thrill,  of splashing like a fountain,   as it raced down the hill.    swoosh! came the water,  flowing fast and swift,  practically going uphill,  carrying objects in a drift.     the water ran smoothly as it rushed past trees,  its bubbles diamonds,  its temperature cold in the breeze.     the water was infinitely fast,  faster than a jaguar,  the water washing rocks and wandering,   as it splashed upon the sandbar.    swish! went the fish as they swam underneath the raging waters that kept them beneath.    the water sped over the edge,  falling off the cliff,  creating a waterfall,  loosening any twigs still stiff.     the water was blue like the sky when clear,  its surface glistening,  and glinting,  so sheer.    finally,  the water  had reached the end,  for seagulls were calling,  and the ocean was around the bend.  the water slowed as it reached the coast a feat that was the end yet provided a boast.    as the fish swam and the waves crashed,  the night set in and the water splashed.    all was silent,  not one sound,  and the moon rose in the background.    the moon had power upon the watery graves,  for as it shone bright,  it continued to make waves.

title: Into the Wild
author: mikaela
text: into the wild    running free with a sense of pride  that burns in me and in the valleys behind  rushing water takes its toll  of all the creatures and thy soul         the wind,  distraught and mystifying  composes its vow to the sky,  to whom is dying   to never leave thee abandoned in shame  for its life is coming to a destined immortal end   our lives are countered to be forsaken  without the untamed winds in our lives  we would be nothing more than an empty forest   that never shall be awakened         with no bramble barriers it is of no use to explore   our world would have no purpose  for there would be no â‘reasonâ’ anymore    a black hearted crow stands frigid and lean  a menacing glare upon his face  scrounging through useless waste  thwart that he is,  a greedy stare catches my glimpse  as i lay a bare    a formless flower shall nurture in peace  projected to be anxious of a place filled with memories of the deceased  an innocent dew rests silently upon the flowers daze  for the flower is lost in a world of unfulfilled dreams  soon to be slain     life;  it is conquered by manâ’s rising power  to create new difficulties  in which we have but no choice to devour  we mustnâ’t run from our true destiny  embrace,  to what our future casts  to close the open door leading to the past   to unlock our fears and triumph over them    to build up our lives; sturdy and strong like a roseâ’s stem  filled with no doubt of the reminiscence  we shall continue to be free   and never again live in the pastâ’s existence    by mikaela t

title: Though comes he
author: mike
text: though comes he,  from the darkness of light,  his appearance was awkward.  once in a blue moon as well,   when he approach the village of mogapeng.  we saw the thunderstorms,  and we knew that he was near yet.  white clouds converted to dark.   darkness of clouds was his second sign.  people went on to prepare for him.  nearly afterwards,  slap of thunder moves,  noise occupies the surrounding villages.   rough and fresh wind blow for long and short.  afterwards,  we heard the tumbling wood,  knocking on top of our houses with the roaring wind shouted above.   birds tumbled through the air,  like small piece of torn paper.  cattle swam like fish in the water.  valleys became seas or oceanic.   farms and agricultural land doomed.  but lives of people remain constant.  house were unharmed as well.  and once more,  the place was liveliness.

title: The sky

text: the sky-  i look up to the sky,  and what do i see? well,  itâ’s none other  than you and me  weâ’re walking along,  not a problem in sight holding each other with our smiles so bright  together we know this dream will never end for eternity,  our hearts will never bend  we continue our walk hand in hand with our feet burning in the sand  with the waves roaring and the stars soaring  we look each other in the eye and cant help but utter a small cry.

title: Chains of torment
author: molli
text: chains of torment  leashed on her tightly are chains that bound,  and chains that eradicate the torment of her sounds.   unable to move,  unable to think,  malice hides deep inside her with increasing links.   the chains speak to her as demons growing bent in the light pilfering hope that any faith of hers are in sight  the shadows leech through her a vortex of haunting dreams.  inside the incarceration the prisoner silently screams  tries to avoid the shadows amid the fear tries to not to cry as the agony unleashes a single tear  it painfully falls to the ground but her voice  cannot yell a single sound  for the chains wraped around her neck plunge into her throat  her cries are unable to escape the coffin in depths of her soul the demon lays his hand upon her  and the bleeding now takes control  sheâ’s all alone as more chains pierce through her skin as she is taunted from the terror within  the arrival of more darkness the impending of the end the decision to die a gift to death her life she now sends  the demons then release the chains but the scar on her face still remains  slowly she disappears unnoticed as if she was never there  as if the chains had never marked her body  as if the demons never crawled into her skin forfeiting her life to receive the win  but in the end they both got their wish for the demon got her soul to cease and from the chains she was released  never to be tied up again. . .

title: Leaping Beyond Freedom
author: molly
text: riding the atv is like swimming with dolphins it is a ride on the wings of eagles.  after an exciting day of riding i lay down to take a tranquility nap.  my white-knuckled hands clench a death-grip on the handles.  in the wind my bug-covered hair sways wildly in the whipping wind.  i feel that i have reached beyond freedom.  i am separated from the problems of the world.  when the daylight turns to dusk,  when my mother calls me for dinner,  i have to say good-bye for awhile… i separated myself from my atv and shake my hands and legs back to reality.  i sadly slide off and slump into a chair by the fire and gaze into space…

title: You
author: naomi
text: my first love was a woman i call natalie.   it was a time when roses turned green and rain never touched your face the sight of her was godly; iridescent.  her laughter was contagious and yet i still went back for more.  between bugs and rainbows  iâ’d say the latter could be just as black.  who is the question.  who  can bring the ocean to our minds  and let it echo like a conch shell.  it is my sadness and my love i dream about at night.   my love for her and  all we did together.   things die and lay to rest.   it leaves a scar but ultimately  itâ’s forever.

title: Beasty Billy
author: naomi
text: while i was in my kitchen baking,   an awful noise something was making,  i turned my head and i observed,  something that seemed quite absurd,  my eyes picked up a creature fowl,  and from its mouth there came a howl,  the monstrous beast: -was exceedingly tall,  -not fearless at all,  -had bright blue hair,  -of eyes it had quite a pair,  its blazing eyes were quietly dripping,  but its brutal hands were noisily ripping,  up my kitchen! 'whats wrong?' i enquired softly at first,  all the time i was expecting the worst,  the beast stopped growling,  prowling,  scowling,  and from its mouth there came no howling,  it spoke with a voice as smooth as silk,  'i'm thirsty,  may i have some milk?' i laughed right then for it seemed silly,  but the beast continued 'my name's billy' 'i'm naomi' i replied 'i'm really nice,  no need to hide' 'the milk's in the fridge,  help yourself' 'and there are cookies on the top shelf' billy lips parted and i saw a grin 'don't mind if i do' and he took down the tin we feasted,  we laughed,  we talked,  we sang,  billy's actually a nice guy too!

title: I'm still your kid
author: natalie
text: once,  as a babe too young to know,  a man was there to help me grow,  i didnâ’t call him â“dad, â” as i was too young to talk,  i suppose for that short while that his heart was unlocked.  we played with toys,  and he fed me a bottle,  when i was so young i could barely waddle.   once,  when i was a kid,  too young to remember,  i had lost an important family member.  not to death,  but to arrogance in the form of more than an ember,  a raging fire consumed his heart.  in the cold and the horrid lonely dark.   you were the dad who was never there who never cared to repair our relationship,  my wings that you clipped,  you left me alone,  to become grown,  all on my own,  without a friend without a father.   i guess i might be a bother to you,  or that you might not even know what youâ’re do -ing to my life and my heart i was broken from the start,  from the moment you decided you werenâ’t ready to be there for me,  to care for me,  to swear to me to always be there by my side that youâ’d always be there if i needed to cry.   you left my life in shambles from the moment i turned one,  the messages were scrambled,   were you there,  were you not,  i didnâ’t know,  they wouldnâ’t stop,  the thoughts that would rush into my head,  â“do you love me? do you care? do you ever plan to be there? why donâ’t you want me? do you hate me? why arenâ’t i good enough? what did i do wrong? was there something i couldâ’ve done before you said â‘so longâ’?â”  but all of these thoughts are wrong because in the end,  you were never really my friend,  you were a jerk who left the first chance he got who about being a father knew not.  who never cared who wasnâ’t there to wipe my tears for fifteen years who doesnâ’t know the pain he causes who made me go through one million losses in one.  except you arenâ’t dead that would be so much easier instead of crying over you iâ’d imagine what youâ’d do instead of saying â“he should call me today but he doesnâ’t careâ” i would be able to say â“he would call me today,  but he canâ’tâ”  because i canâ’t deal with the fact that youâ’ll never love me.  i canâ’t deal with the fact that iâ’ll never have a father.  i canâ’t deal with the fact that iâ’ll never have you.   because iâ’m still your kid.  but you refuse to be my dad.

title: Deeper Than
author: nesha
text: deeper than the hand could touch,  deeper than the rivers,  stream and such.   deeper than the rising swelling sea,  deeper than all this pain you've given me.   deeper than my soul can feel,  deeper than the wounds can't heal.   deeper than this pool of misery,  deeper than any eye could see.   deeper than any passion could reach,  deeper and far more complicated than any lesson you could teach.   deeper than all the rushing oceans much deeper than my hurt  and emotions.   this thing that is deeper than all above is the strongness and deepness of my love.   i tried,  but i can no longer hide,  all this passion i have for you inside.   no matter how bad you break my heart,   or cause me to fall apart i'll always love you.   i guess no matter what you do i'll always come back to you.  this deepness that connects me with your heart,  and intertwines me with your soul makes me complete makes me whole.   deeper than the part of the pool your feet can barely touch,  this is how deep i love you,  this is how much.

title: If I had wings
author: peter
text: if i had wings  i would fly as high as to where the angels sing,   not looking back so i wont get attacked by all the bad memories,   for every look back is a step back and every step back is no step forward so why do that and not move toward the goal that you have,   and you do have one,   even if the path there isnâ’t fun,  or maybe its foggy and you just cant see but donâ’t worry,   because it is there and you will never have to share the success that it brings you because you and only you passed the very customized test designed just for you.   and yes the test is lond and full of surprise,  full of kicks and punches to knock you down and then come the long lasting cries,   but they were worth it,   because you could never make a sound of defeat you just had to get up and say i cant be beat!  and right when you think thatâ’s it,  then push you down a pit.   this is rock bottom,  a place you must climb out of but how can you if there are no walls,  no one their to support you.   youâ’re not truly rock bottom if you even have one friend  because itâ’s a place that feels like it has no end,   just a bottomless pit full of sadness and sorrow,   a place where for you,  there might not be a tomorrow.    but i just want you to know that if you can take one giant leap out of that abyss,  you wont have to miss anything of what you didnâ’t have,  because at that moment you have conquered the test,  because after rock bottom is only success.

title: Love ain't simple
author: phat
text: love is transparent,  a window you can see through,  at times fogged up by the cold,  frozen with deceit and lies.   love is a window,  easily shattered by the raging tornado.  ain't mended,  ain't shaped,  ain't back to its lovely form again.   if only love was gold and metal,  windows gold and metal.  then no tornado could tear them apart.  if only love was simple.   but if love was simple,  then its purpose is defeated.  i rather have love as it is,  and taste both bitter and sweet.

text: through all the many fights we have had all those nights spent crying over you what was i to do forget you or forgive you  i kept thinking about us what we have been through was i to throw it away or was i to keep you  but then i think how you look me in the eyes so deeply in love are we to be forever or a relationship severed  through all that i know your love for me is true i canâ’t let you go i made that promise to you forever and always  i canâ’t live without you in my life you are now a part of it always a part of my life now a piece of my heart that will be there for eternity  our love grows everyday stronger and stronger never to be broken i swear that to you  i would make that commitment to stay at your side the rest of my life you and me to the very end  i love you

title: We will meet again
author: plaksha
text: we will meet again (a poem by every mother who has lost her child)  i will never ask god  why did he give me you. . . . .    i remember the day you were born,   after hearing you cry i just knew that i would never be forlorn.   when you held my finger refusing to let it go,   i just knew that you would never make me feel low.    i will never ask god  why did he give me you. . . . .    your eyes seemed like a medicine for my griefs,   it all seemed like a moment too brief.   and then you little kiss made me feel happier than i had ever been,   it gave me an assuring serenity much unseen   i will never ask god  why did he give me you. . . .    but when you just slept and never woke up,   i wanted it all to end like a bad dream.   after a lot of prayers i finally gave up  i saw you in your ashes and just wanted to scream    i will never ask god  why did he give me you,   nor will i ask him  why he had to take, too.   i will never let my tears rain  because i am sure that we will meet again. . . . . . .

title: The Shadow
author: renee
text: darkness swallows me whole, as i follow your every move to keep up with you is my goal. the sun towers over me, >making me exist. run faster, the words linger on your lips. quickly, i stay within your path making sure i mirror your image attesting all of your beauty, expanding your real existence. it becomes a game for me to play, chasing you each and every day, i make sure to stay behind never crossing the line. distortion of the light, creates me not at night, but during the day i appear in different forms of cheer i fabricate happiness, for now you know you are there. i seem different and interchangeable, as often you take me for granted. still i am here, behind you as i listen, your shadow always near.

title: Anazlyzing Apperences
author: rhiannon
text: every day as i enter inside my classroom,  stood a girl who looked smart and bright,  she took out her books,  and started to study.  her beautiful smile was big and bright just like a light,  all though her attitude was a little crummy.   but her appearance made her look innocent and sweet,  and she had always kept her work very neat.   she sounded calm and at eased with her talking,  and as light as a butterfly with her walking.   but people were becoming jealous because of what she acquired,  instead of bragging all she did was let them admire.  she found it easy to hide her sadness,  and then tried to replace it with gladness.   but one day that was so glumly and long,  she sat in a corner and began to cry.  people began to wonder what was wrong,  everyone had asked her â“why are you cryingâ”,  but she only replied with â“i donâ’t know whyâ”.   she said her sadness was getting worse,  but everyone ignored her,  and it left her in a curse.

title: My Goddess
author: rickey
text: brown hair dancing on delicate shoulders and a gentle glow to tan a perfect face with a voice to mock all the choirs of angels and eyes chestnut and round deep enough to captivate any mortal.  \tshe is a goddess.  \tshe is my goddess.  and yet i am forbidden to speak to her.  no,  no not forbidden,  but afraidâ— too afraid to wave a hand,  too afraid to even murmur a mellow â“helloâ”,  convinced that her response would be my undoing.  so i wait,  watching from afar and even though i may never speak to her and even though she may never know i exist,  i will still worship her as the goddess she is.          she is a goddess.          she is my goddess.

title: Reminders
author: riley
text: she reminds me of silk,  she reminds me of gold,  of things that are precious,  of things that are bold.  she reminds me of fire burning,  bright in the dark,  her heart an inferno,  yet lit by a spark.  all started out small,  but grew to be great,  she's now lighting my fire,  deciding my fate.  what started out small and burned to a scar,  reminds me of reasons we made it that far.  i want to go further,  with her by my side,  i want to walk straighter,  i need back my pride.  i'm walking on gravel,  burned by the stone,  i'm now living in hell,  tourtured,  alone.  i cxan now see the footsteps,  the path in the ash,  leading further down hell like a blood dripping gash.  the blood has stopped dripping,  now pouring like rain,  it reminds me of heartache,  it reminds me of pain.  she flies like a phoenix,  graceful and swift,  it reminds me of burdons,  great weights i can't lift.  so i sit in my hell,  down and depressed,  lay my head in my hands,  and cry like the rest.

title: Somewhere is and there we will be
author: riley
text: there; we're here.  now we're getting somewhere.  but we should be,  because we have to be going somewhere sometime,  and sometime is always.  if we're not going somewhere,  weâ’re here; and yet,  if somewhere is elsewhere,  then elsewhere is where we'll be.  but if weâ’re not where elsewhere is,  then somewhere is where we're not,  therefore,  weâ’re right where we are.  and right where we are is always someplace.  therefore,  weâ’re always someplace if we're not somewhere,  and elsewhere is always nearby.  and nearby is always right where it should be.   so there.

title: The Perfect Day

text: i start the day and wake up to hellos,  get up from my bed and stare at the skies,  i slip on my clothes and go with the flow,  i feel free and relaxed and ever so wise.   i rush down the stairs to devour my meal,  there was chicken soup,  i engorged it whole,  i had a strange blur,  it felt so unreal,  something had a hold of me and my soul.   i then stood up and went to my soft couch,  called for my dog companion to play,  i went out and took a toy from my pouch,  me and my boy had lots of fun all day.   we played until dawn,  he found a big bone,  this is how it feels to not be alone.

title: Alone
author: rose
text: under the sliver moon,  under the twinkling stars,  is the sole place where i can be my true self.  if only you knew who i really could be. . .  i let my heart out of its' cage and my soul is set free.  it wanders all over the world but always close to home.  i try to let my true colors show but i never can.  i'm always acting,  being,  seeing someone else.  everything fades away once the sun rises.  the moon takes my words away,  and the sun dries up my beauty.  as if the world wanted to forget who i was.  who i am.  deep down inside,  i am alone.  my soul is black,  twisted,  and evil.  and it makes me want to be dead.  but i now realize that i am dead.  my heart doesn't beat.  i cannot feel.  i am cold and lifeless.  and yet i'm still here. . .  why can't i drift away like a leaf on the wind. . .

title: This Love
author: rosemary
text: this love, one that has found me from way far found me like a needle in stacks of hay.  what i feel for him is not bizzare,  but gut filled with butterflies waiting to sway.   we are different inside and out,  yet our emotions run wild without a leash.  i know deep inside he does not regret and so,  is this love really meant to be?  he is as fragile as a china doll.  his skin as smooth as a baby's bottom.  his gentle voice replies when i call ''paul. '' delicate hands soft as bedsheet cotton.   his presence relieves my burden of cold.  this love,  one that i will always behold.

title: My First Flight
author: rosey
text: the plane was just about ready to take off.  the flight attendant was named freddie goff.  my stomach wasn't doing all that good,   my little brother was crying for food.   freddie was instructing us.  i was thinking we could've taken a bus.  i put on my seat belt and made it tight,  for i'd feel safer on the flight.    both my younger brothers were doing fine.  i look at my watch,  it was just about nine.  the pilot told us to be seated,  and hoping it wasn't to be repeated.   the plane finally started down the runway.  and was just about to fly away.  the turbulance was shaking us.  now i was really hoping we should've taken the bus.   freddie came over and asked ''any drinks or food?'' i was kind of hungry and wanted some peanuts that everyone say are so good.  i looked out the window and saw nothing but the clouds in the sky.  this was the first time i was on anything that could fly.

title: Control
author: sabrina
text: something inside of me screams,  screams to get out of this force holding me in.  screams to break the authority,   to rise to the surface and breathe fresh air.   i tell myself i am in control,  but inside i know that it has the power,  has the power on what i say,  what i think,  what i feel,  why canâ’t i be free?  i wish i could break free,   but it is going to always be a part of me.  i try and try to forget what happened,  but it all keeps coming back.   the way i felt,  what was done how could such a small action be in so much control? inside i scream to be free,  to live my life like i did before.  but it is holding me back.   if i could go back to the night,  the night it took control what would i change? would i avoid it knowing what i would miss? would i not go at all?  it has the control and i need to get out,  out of its power and its authority.  how,  how do i break free? i do not know,  so iâ’ll have to listen to my screams.

text: i don't want pity  so don't pity me  i am not allowed to pity myself  your pity isn't making me stronger its making me weaker  i tell you not for pity but so i know that two people in my life won't judge  if you understand where i come from  you won't be able to judge  who i am  what i am  what i do  is based on where i'm from   so don't pity me i don't need you pity  nor do i need my own  i don't need the judgement from you i get it from the world  enough to point out my imperfections  enough to tell me every move i make  is wrong  i don't want the sympathy.  i want the change  you think i'm fishing for complemets  or wanting you to feel sorry for me i meerly wan't o understand what you see  but don't tell me based on what i've told you  i need you to be honest cause with out honesty there is no us and which hurts more  us with honesty or no us at all  it takes time  when something you think you'll have forever goes away  and then other things soon follow.    there are dates that hurt they come around yearly  makeing it nearly impossible to forget for a moment that these events have occured.   why should i tell you  well i thought you'd understand but you think that i wan't what i don't   so don't give me your pity for if you do  it weakens me  and when i'm weak where do i go i come crawling back   but not for your pity for your strength

title: If I Can Only Make You See
author: sarah
text: why don't you ever call me? if i can only make you see how much you mean to me,  then maybe you will feel the way i do.  people tell me you're not worth it,  but i just tell them to stop having a fit.  we were meant to be,  you and i,  me and you.  no matter how hard people try they just can't break through.  sometimes i sit alone in my room and listen to the sadest songs i can find.  thinking maybe soon i will get a call from you.  but i sit and wait until i can no longer stand it and i force myself to go to another room.  my life is nothing without you,  when your around me my face shines up like a new shoe,  but when you're gone i have no clue.  sometimes i think we were better off as friends,  but i know no matter what happens our friendship won't have any bends.  i really care for you,  and i hope you feel the same way about me.  our friends think that we are just two kids that don't know what love is,  but they are wrong.  before i met you there was an emptiness inside me,  and now i have finally found the key.  now if i can only make you see how much you mean to me.

title: The Speck in my Eye
author: sarah
text: oh,  how i dread eight hours within four walls.  it would be awesome if these walls could talk.  whether in the classroom or in the halls,  now and then i wish there was a beanstalk.   i would climb so high that faces would fade.  truly,  what a diversion that would be.  propelling above those hurt and betrayed,  by dispassionate words conveyed in glee.   no matter the color,  the size,  or height,   each tender,  afflicted soul bleeds the same.  ducking in rooms,  lying low,  out of sight,  hovering up,  i almost feel their pain.   so long as my descent is faintly sly,  perhaps they wonâ’t see the speck in my eye.

title: Parents prayer
author: scott
text: now i lay me down to sleep,  i pray my sanity to keep.  for if some peace i do not find,  i'm pretty sure i'll lose my mind.    i pray i find a little quiet,  far from the daily family riot.  may i lie back and not have to think about what they're stuffing down the sink,   or who they're with,  or where they're at and what they're doing to the cat.  i pray for time all to myself (did something just fall off a shelf?)  to cuddle in my nice,  soft bed (oh no,  another goldfishâ—dead!) some silent moments for goodness sake (did i just hear a window break?)  and that i need not cook or clean (well heck,  i've got the right to dream) yes now i lay me down to sleep,  i pray my wits about me keep,   but as i look around i know,  i must have lost them long ago!

text: swimming,  searching,  finding prey,  letting its senses guide the way.  closer,  closer to its food,  fins and teeth as its tools.  closer,  closer his prey's in sight,  tensing up for his fight.  closer,  closer about to attack,  so close its almost on its prey's back.  teeth ripping,  shredding,  killing,  fish eaten food fulfilling.  all in the day of a hungry shark.

title: Morning of Mourning
author: stefanie
text: the dawn came upon the sleepy town; few were awake from their sleeping state.  she looked out the window,  and pondered it all.  wondering how everything could seem normal,  so soon after the tragedy had befallen.   laying awake in her tearing state,  she sighed.  the morning of mourning had finally come,  and no one could know how much emotion the day held.  she tried to laugh,  but no sound could surpass this eerie silence that had captured the day.   this was the day,  in a few short hours everything would go back to normal.  like nothing had happened.  she,  again started to cry,  wondering why they had to go.  it was their choice,  but still she just didnâ’t know.  they went to fight,  and knowing the danger kept on fighting.  for our rights.   â“though gone,  its not goodbye.  itâ’s see you later,  until another time.  we will meet again,  and be together with no end. â” the pastor said,  at the funeral , and it painted a mural of hope in her mind.  it still would be some time,  but she would again see his face.  he had gone to iraq; a decision made in haste.   â“to protect you,  and the rest, â” he said.  â“thatâ’s why i must leave.  i love you so much,  but you must let me go.  no matter what happens we will always be together.  goodbye little sister.  please donâ’t cry. â” the tears ceased,  she did the only thing she could do.  she whispered,  â“big brother i love you too. â”

title: Addiction
author: stephaine
text: you are an addiction,   when im with you theres no prediction.   ever forget who you are?  ever feel like youve made things go till they went to far?  you wanted them to begin,   but eventually your world began to spin.   you let him hold your heart,   until he tore your world apart.   dont give anyone that chance,   dont let anyone put you under a trance.   he might make you feel that unlike everyone else he is not the same,   if you believe him all the way than you are partly to blame.   you want a relationship that will be secure,   but in the end for love there is no cure.

title: I am
author: stephanie
text: i am the stalker who walks at night.  i wonder what's coming for me.  i hear the soft click of claws.  i see a shadow creeping behind me.  i want to know who's following me.  i am the stalker who walks at night.   i pretend that i have the ability to stop what's happening.  i feel life draining from me.  i touch the skin of those i love.  i worry i'll never see them happy again.  i cry knowing i will never be clean.  i am the stalker who walks at night.   i understand all that has happened to me.  i say i will be alright.  i dream i will never see that face again.  i try to tell myself that i won't.  i hope he won't come looking.  i am the stalker who walks at night.

title: The Color of Love
author: symiah
text: he's a boy,  he's just a boy he's not some hoodlum or vandal he's a boy,  just another boy so how come when she speaks of him,  some disapprove?  after all he's just a boy but a boy of a different complexion  we are all just human beings just small forms of life in this endless universe she says she is an artist,  and she sees beauty wherever it lies she sees beauty in her race,  but in his as well if his pigment was as dark as hers,  would you then approve? if her skin was as light as his,  would you then accept her?  we live in a world with an array of colors we live on an earth with a variety of perspectives she chose a less narrow path she chose to be color blind  that was her choice she didn't choose to be a sinner she didn't choose to cause others pain she chose to be happy because he may just be a boy,  a boy of a different complexion but he saw the brightness in a dark woman and she saw that even his light skin had endless depths of mystery  our ancestor's colors clashed but here we are in a generation where our colors are able to compliment each other  so widen the paths of narrow minds don't just broaden your horizon,  add an array of color to it.   we are all works of art god created her,  god created him they are both god's muse,  though it may not seem like beauty to you  at the end of it all he is just a boy,  she is just a girl and it is all the same love love love knows no color she may be one race,  he may be another but if you cut them both with the same blade of truth,  they both bleed the same color the color of humans,  the color of life,  te color of love maybe that's what we need to focus on. .

title: EVERYTIME

text: as the world closes in on this thing called me,   i wonder if i'll ever get out,  ever cure completly,  i wanna take a deep breath,  suck it all in,  but everytime i take a step i commit another sin.    my wrists still bleed with invisible blood,  untill it's up to my neck,  one massive flood,  i wanna stop the bleeding,  the cutting,  the pain,  but everytime i try,  my blood pours out like rain.    i stare at the ground to all the dry tears i've cried,  their all there,  not one absorbed,  not one dried,  i wanna stop the tears from falling and hitting the ground,  but everytime i dry my tears another problems found.    i look at the rope that is meant to be around my neck,   then i glance at the mirror and see that i'm a wreck,  i want to stop choking on the air i need,  but everytime i say something,  my mouth fills up with greed.    i listen to the music that talks all about death,  with every beat i take a deep breath,  i wanna turn it off,  shut down it's persuasion,  but everytime i add it up,  it still equals the same equation.    as the world closes in on this thing called me,   i wonder if i'll ever get out,  ever cure completly,  i wanna take a deep breath,  suck it all in,  but everytime i take a step i commit another sin.

title: All I wanted to say
author: tara
text:
how i miss you. oh! how you're on my mind. it's been awhile, and still i wish you were still here. i never got to say goodbye, or that i thought you are a great guy, or how much you meant to everyone, even though you didn't know, i didn't get to tell you, how you made us all smile, with your silly happy moments, in the kitchen, just singing your heart out with mom and missy, just making us all laugh. now for as it will be the new year, and instead of giving you a party hat, we will be giving you a bouquet, to set aside your grave. i am so sorry that i couldn't see you, before you went. oh! how i regret it so bad, but, i know in my heart, that you can hear me now, and all i wanted to say, is hi and i hope, you are having a good 'ole time, just partyin' with your old
\nhomeboys. and so now i leave, with this one little phrase, you are loved, and will be loved, but most of all you are remembered, and will be remembered for life.

title: ~*~LOVE~*~
author: tara
text: ~*~love, ~*~  what is love? people throw the word around.  is it a phrase? a feeling,  a meaningful word? should it have meaning? should it matter?  ~*~my answer to that is yes. ~*~ yes,  it is a phrase.  yes,  it is a feeling.  yes,  it should have meaning.  yes,  it should matter.   ~*~why?~*~ the question now is,   why? why is it a phrase? why do people through the word around? why is it a feeling of happiness? why should it have meaning? why should it matter?  ~*~my answers are, ~*~  it's a phrase because it is grammar.  lol people through it around because they don't understand love.  it is a good feeling because you know he is the one for you.  it should have meaning because it is a powerful word that says how people feel.  it should matter because it is a strong feeling of compassion that no one could ever take away.   ~*~you ask, '' have you been in love, ~*~ how do you know,   what does it feel like?'' yes,  i have been in love.  you can just tell that you love someone.  love is like a roller coaster.  at first you get nervous,  you get butterflies,  then you get afraid.  afraid that you will get hurt.  then you know that he'll never hurt you,  and that he'll always be there.  you know that you are in love because all that you want to do is be with that person.  you want to be near that person.  you want to feel the comforting touch of him that lets you know that everything is ok,  and no matter what anyone does he'll always stand up for you.  you know because that person is the only one you want to see.  this is how i know that i am in love.  after i think about it and i think about the questions i still say that my answers are yes.  yes it does matter,  it is a feeling,  and it does matter.  this is how i feel about you and i just wanted to say: ~*~i love you!~*~

text: i sat taking a glance outside before closing my eyes   my music was blasting i thought over everything my mother had told me,  how couldnâ’t i have noticed it was all lies? i thought my childhood happiness would be everlasting   i guess we all have to wake up at some point in time  i jolted backwards before i soared through the air  and i thought maybe the past was my sour lime  happiness is kind of like paper,  being fast and easy to tear      as i glided i remembered the incident   the loud bang and the thump of her body hitting the ground  i should have known because he acted around me the same way; it was a clear hint  and then there was only one thing i could hear as that foul man ran out the door; that memorable ringing sound      maybe it was because she was a forgiving person  the wheels of the plane thump and roll across earth's rock  and maybe since i am her son  maybe i will be able to forgive,  after all one day each personâ’s hands will cease to move on each individualâ’s life-timed alarm clock

text: i watch tears trickle down from the reckless.  theyâ’re the ones who are arrogant,  and self-centered.  they think that they were better than everyone else.  they had all that they had ever wanted; for a while.  then they lost it all.  jesus once met a rich man who had asked him how he could be completely righteous and he answered,  â“take all that you have and sell it or give it away. â” the man who was there was distressed in this news,  and so he went and did as the lord told him so.  the man had many things one day,  and nothing the next.  i watch tears trickle down from the reckless.  \tthey are the ones who brag about everything,  like being first,  and love only themselves.  they could be the rich,  married couple that lose everything they loved,  due to a tragedy.  for that,  they weep and wish to redeem themselves.  our god knows who did this and he punished them for their sins.  in the book acts,  a man named saul was on his way to damascus to persecute christians when the lord blinded him.  he cried out and prayed for two days when his sight was restored,  and he followed godâ’s command.  i watch tears trickle down from the reckless.

title: I Feel Hope In The Depressed
author: timothy
text: i feel hope in the depressed.  there are those who are emotionally depressed,  and those who are physically depressed.  those who are emotionally depressed have had family struggles or issues with friends.  the physically depressed are diagnosed with depression,  and are lonely,  quiet,  shy,  and often seen looking down.  but there are medicines for both: the lord,  the bible,  medical drugs,  and those who ae close to you.  i feel hope in the depressed.  \tthere are those who will support you,  uplift you,  and help you.  but if the oneâ’s close to you are your problems,  then look to god,  for he will be with you every second of every day.  psalm 23:1-4 says,  â“the lord is my shepherd,  i lack nothing.  he makes lie down in green pastures,  he leads me beside quiet waters,  he refreshes my soul.  he guides me along the right paths for his nameâ’s sake.  even though i walk through the valley of the shadow of death,  i will fear no evil,  for you are with me; your rod and your staff,  they comfort me. â” i feel hope in the depressed.  \tthose who have physical depression,  there is medicine in him,  and in medical drugs.  they are meant to help you specifically,  and will make you feel better.  theyâ’ll give you the strength to be happy,  and the will to be strong.  depression has to be fought,  and we will win.  i feel hope in the depressed.

title: Christmas on Barking Street
author: tito
text: christmas eve was officially here,  bringing to barking street holiday cheer.   in the little pink house,  so cozy and neat,  the chihuahuas welcomed christmas to barking street.   the chihuahuas all joined in the grand feast,  not a worry or trouble,  not in the least.   down the street a family of hounds had nothing to eat,  so the chihuahuas made them a plate of ham,  roast lamb,  and potted meat.   the chihuahuas learned the true meaning of christmas that christmas eve,  that it is better to give than to receive!

title: ''Hello Me''

text: hello me \twhy don't you understand, \t\t \tyou can change \tyou can be a different man.  \t \tyou have had a history \tfor only bad will come,  \tit could all get better \tyou need to change what you have done.  \t \tdont be weak \tfor you are strong,  \tlet your sadness go \tplease don't do wrong.  \t \tfor you know better  \tand you know what to do,  \tdon't try to be someone else \tfor you are you.  \t \tdon't say your nothing \tdon't do harmful things,  \tfor you should do this \t \tuntil you hear the angels sing.   \tyou have been smoking \twhich just killed half your life,  \twhy don't you just quit it\t \tuntil you have a wife.  \t \tyou have rubbed snuff \tthe worst thing there is to do,  \tdont show that your scared \tjust be you.   \twhen you are happy  \tjust smile and dont worry about it,  \tit will give you a better life \tyou won't have such a fit.   \tthere are things you have done  \tthings that are untold,  \tif you become happy now \tyour life wont be so cold.   \tyou have let yourself give up  \tyou have given up too long,  \tdon't give up any more \tjust stay strong.  \t \twhen someone says you're stupid \tdont give them what they want,  \tbecause they will put you down \tevery day and every month.   \tlet yourself cry \tlet yourself show emotion,  \tyou dont need a spell  \tyou dont need a potion.   \teven if it is stupid \teven if it is lame,  \tdon't criticize yourself as a ''no one'',  \tfor you'll always be the same.   \tif you let your heart bleed \tif you let everything back in your soul,  \tyou will have nothing to be proud of \tyou don't have to act like your cool.   \tyou are what you want to  \tyou are what you seem to be,  \tit's not what you think it is \tit's only what you see.   \tso this is a voice \tthat tells you that you dont have to fight,  \tfight for something  \tjust fight for something that is right.

title: Water day
author: trent
text: \tevery part of my body was overwhelmed by what i took in.  it absorbed in my bones.  it held on to me and would not let go.  i did not want it to let go.  i wanted to stay in that moment in time forever.  there were smells,  colors and the temperature.  \tthe smells  flew all around my body as i took each one of them in.    they came up from the ground.   down form the trees,  and circled around me from the air.    the scent was powerful but calming.   it aloud you to think and to dream.   as the scents filled my nose the colors filled my eyes.   \tthe colors.   all around me,    it took me into a phsicadelia.   they entranced my stare so that almost at once they all morphed together.   they were the leaves on the trees.   the grass on the ground.   the water in the stream.   as they all came together they made one great color.    even though my eyes watered they held on to there position not daring to blink and lose the color.    the sights were taken away by the arctic wind that circled around me chilling me to the bone \tthe colors  i was dead frozen,  my breath was shown to the woods.   i was unable to move for my body would not respond.   the weather was cold and damp which made the whole woods damp.   thus weakening the color illusion.   the smells were gone,  for my nose was unable to move.   it was not able to reach back and smell.  i was cold.   \ti was out in the woods smelling the smells,  observing the sights and colors.  being chilled by the the cold wind.  the woods is were people come to peace.  a sense of relaxation,  harmony.  they are able to let go of there struggles there stresses.  this feeling is the greatest a person can have.  the feeling of,  happiness.

title: Snow in her hair

text: cry,  donâ’t listen what they say  â‘cause this is the best way   to leave your feelings fall.   just make it how you want  and let your story to be told.   say sorry,  and go on  make your actions to be done.   listen,  donâ’t let them knock you down  â‘cause this is your time  you should move now.   donâ’t think that they are right  because you can win,   you can show your light,   that is hidden inside.   donâ’t let you haters talk  show them who you are  go and attack!  and donâ’t be so scared  â‘cause you can live only once   god gave you only one chance,   and that big fear   should already disappear  because there are a lot of problems  that should be forgotten forever.   are you still crying?  if you are than stop right now  and let that tears fall for the last time down.   but if youâ’re not crying   than good job,   youâ’re not lying.   now,  go!  and let them know  that youâ’re not lonely,   that you have friends  and youâ’re not the only  that hates his enemies.   hey,  are you ready?  than get started!  letâ’s play a game  where youâ’ll be the main  and those who were talking aloud  now they wouldnâ’t make even a sound.  congratulations,  you won.   the game is done,   and the enemies are gone.   relax for a moment  and remember who you are,   how far you got.   just know that life is a game  and you canâ’t anyone blame  if you loose  or if youâ’re confused.   just live it how is meant   and it will be alright.

text: i see you leave marks on my paper as i guide you with my hand with your wooden body and your painted clothes the pressure i put on you as i write my words the paper begins to smudge as i guide you,  i make mistakes as your tip becomes weak because of the pressure i put on you i sharpen,  to make you strong again as i put my thoughts onto paper,  i guide you to create my words the words that my lips will never say i write i will keep writing and writing and writing untill,  you break i look at you now,   your broken body in half i look at you now now that you are broken,  you are no more

text: i could not sleep and i stepped out,  it was all alone and there was no shout.  i moved forward and saw a creeping small snail,  it was moving to a bush because it was at time of hail.  the moon brightly shone,  at a new plant that was just grown.  i took a plant with  flower,  and gave it a nice shower.  from another side my dog in pain started to weep,  i touched her face and gave her a nice sleep.  the moving cold breeze,  that was coming from huge green trees.  these all dissolved my sleep,  then i took a breath deep.  nature gave me a beautiful night sight,  altogether it was a pleasant night.          thankyou

title: Betrayal
author: victoria
text: i am quiet and unpredictable.  you cannot hear me coming.   whoever falls for my tricks,  falls deep into despair.   i seem comforting and beautiful,   yet i lash out as soon as you become weak.   i am always there,  following your every move.   i devour your suffering.   your eyes glisten with sadness,  i laugh in delight.   you come back hoping i was just a lie. . .   but darling,  i am not a lie.   i despise your happiness.  love is no true emotion.   i am here to destroy your heart.   i want to hear your heart shatter,   i want to see you fall.   you can never escape me,  darling.   be careful. . .   i hide in the shadow of a person's soul.   you will never see me coming.   it is best. . .   to not trust at all.

title: Hide
author: victoria
text: dearest my soul,   why do you betray me so?  you were born so sweet. . .  so innocent.   what ever happened?  dearest my shadows,   why do you embrace me so tightly?  i thank you for concealing my sorrows.   why must the sun conquer your darkness?  i clutch your comfort so tightly. . .   dearest my heart,   you've vanished from sight. . .   my pleasure is diminished.   my misery has vanquished my smile.   i ask you;  why?  dearest my sorrows,  thank you.   your comfort has aided me.   sorrow. . .  my one and only friend.   dearest the angels,  would it be wrong to join you? would they judge me,   for chasing your freedom?  dearest my haven,  your solitude eases my torment.   without you,  my despair would triumph.   i thank your loyalty.   i yearn for your seclusion.   i'm sorry dear sunlight.   i loved your shine,  your glimmer.   i adored your beauty.   but eventually the darkness returns.   and everything you once found beautiful,   will yet again perish.

title: Goodbye
author: victoria
text: goodbye is a stab of reality  that kills your soul  and eats  your heart    pain;  the inevitable reminder  that you're still alive    infatuation;  a beautiful storm  that destroys your compassion    help. . .   the desperate cry that  no one hears    courage~  the strength to rise  and keep fighting    friends  the beautiful tape that  holds you together.

title: Dreams
author: vidhi
text: dream! dream !dream! a small word with thousands of meaning.  dare to dream dare to try.  the only way to touch the sky.  dreams make you happy,  dreams make you cry.  but believe me they are the happiest think you achieve in your life.  your passion is your real dream your real friend.  they are made for you and you are made for them.  right from birth  till the death.  they are ones which always push you ahead . dreams are ones which never let you fall . they will not make you failure but they will make you strong i dare to dream,  l dare  to try because they are ones which will always make me fly high.

title: In My Room
author: virginia
text: and in my room,  the candles glow,  the dying sun,  the curtains flow.  i dream a dream,  the breath of life,  the thought of you,  removes my strife.  feelings changing,   time goes by,  a shadowed room,  i lie down and cry.  once was than,  is no more,  threw me in a room,  and locked the door.  the rain falls down,  like tears from above,  no trust no feelings,  no feelings no love.  and in my room,  the candles glow,  the dying sun,  the curtains flow.

title: Nightmare
author: virginia
text: we hide in shadows,  more scared than before,  it's like i'm standing in a room,  with no windows no doors.  and in my room,  the light does glow,  the night is young,  has yet to grow.  from dusk to dawn,  march to may,  things are growing,  more every day.  i begin to see things,  people dancing,  empty rooms,  yet people chanting.  yet in the dark,  all the while,  evil grows,  an evil smile.

title: All Gone Wrong
author: virginia
text: oak trees grow,  flowers bloom,  summer comes,  all too soon.  to live a life,  and feel the pain,  the sun goes down,  it begins to rain.  the love we had,  now all is lost,  all is gone,  all is tossed.  just as the rain,  the tears pour down,  they land so gracefully,  upon the ground.  then as you leave,  i'm anchored down,  the tide comes in,  i'll surely drown.  a rose can hold beauty,  along with pain,  just as tears fall down,  and then commeth the rain.

title: Lost
author: virginia
text: i'm going in circles,  i cannot find the way,  going through a laybrinth,  i think i've gone astray.  no one right there for me,  i've lost my way again,  you took my hand and helped me through,  your my only friend.  i'm lost in a maze of troubles,  fighting to find my way,  i can not find what i'm looking for,  i'm farther every day.  my feet are growing tired,  i'm wearier every day,  not walk but glide,  rolling,  float,  sashay.  i see the world around me,  it spins around,  i begin to fall,  i'm trapped now under ground.  it's only forever,  not long at all,  i'm lost and i'm lonley,  i panic then i fall.  i'm going in circles,  i cannot find the way,  going through a laybrinth,  i know i've lost my way.

title: Best Friends For life
author: virginia
text: i met you in the beginning,  i knew we'd get along,  but then i had found out,  i'm moving,  i'll be gone.  you helped me through my troubles,  i know you really cared,  and in the time of trouble,  you were always there.  we'll always be best friends,  we'll go on in spirit and heart,  and though were not together,  we'll never,  be apart.

title: Spirit
author: virginia
text: in spirit i'll always love you,  despite all the problems we've had,  and yet i know we've fought,  you never made me mad.  i laughed with you i cried with you,  and this will surely show,  i'm friends with you forever,  in spirit and in soul.

title: Always There
author: virginia
text: when i was lost,  you always found me,  i began to fall,  you always caught me.  when i was down,  you picked me up,  you took my hand,  and helped me up.  so when i'm swimming,  in a sea of tears,  you've held my hand,  through sadness and fears.  and when the rain falls,  and i'm all alone,  your light comes through,  and brightness shone.  and in the dark,  i cannot see,  i thought of you,  you set me free.  you're always there,  you come around,  and free me from,  these ropes i'm bound.

title: Stars Beyond The Horizon
author: virginia
text: i look up to the sky,  and gaze into the stars,  i look apon the brightest one,  it seems so very far.  i sit and watch the sunset,  then watch the moon to rise,  then the stars one by one,  till i'm ready to walk inside.  the stars above and far beyond,  the horizon seem so few,  but theres so many more we can not see,  so many stars are new.  and when the morning begins to show,  and we start a day thats new,  the sun comes up to brings us light,  and along with it the dew.

title: Reach Out
author: virginia
text: sometimes i feel,  like i am all alone,  but then i look back,  and i feel i have grown.  reach out in the darkness,  if you cannot find your way,  reach out in the darkness,  when the skies are turning gray.  and when you cant find love,  it seems you've gone astray,  love will come to you,  somehow,  it will find a way.

title: Him
author: virginia
text: filled with fear,  filled with hate,  anger hatred,  coruption,  frustrate.  why won't he leave me,  leave me alone,  writes me those letters,  calls on the phone.  he calls again,  my minds all a mess,  i'll call him back,  768- can't remember the rest.  getting so dizzy,  i'm so confused,  i don't want him back,  i dont know what to do.  yet he won't stop calling,  keeps making me mad,  as if i'm not upset enough already,  then he brings up his dad.  i hate the way he talks,  i hate the things he'll do,  i don't know how i feel for him,  and i'm still so very confused.  i need someone to talk to,  but the closest ones not there,  i need someone to help me through,  i hate it,  it's not fair.  the road i walk is narrow,  the sky is dull and grey,  the grass is greener on the other side,  so very far away.  i hate the life i'm living,  i need to get away from him,  but i am yet so very confused,  love,  hate,  corruption,  sin.

title: The Artist
author: wenting
text: a thin dab of paint<br>graces the end of the brush. <br>a smile eases across her faceâ—<br>thereâ’s no need to rush. <br>hand reaches out, <br>adjusting paper â’til all is just right. <br>gently tilting the bowl, <br>watching water catch light. <br>open window lets the table<br>be soaked in golden sun. <br>sheâ’s mixing and swirling, <br>letting the colors run. <br>looking up,  she sees<br>a bird perching outside. <br>its song mingles with summer, <br>its yellow beak open wide. <br>she sits and keeps vigil<br>of the world beyond the sky, <br>observing and listening to those<br>unseen by the human eye. <br>the glowing orb up above<br>fades slowly into the twilight. <br>still,  she makes no move, <br>and holds the brush tight. <br>darkness begins to fall, <br>but she sees it not. <br>then finally,  in the night, <br>she finds what she has sought. <br>dancing the brush across paper, <br>flecking white with blue, <br>she gazes again upon her subject<br>with interest anew. <br>she works hard to capture beauty<br>from nightfall â’til dawn, <br>even as morning began<br>to creep across the lawn. <br>finally,  her hand lowers, <br>and she lets the brush fall. <br>it had taken hours, <br>but sheâ’d painted it all. <br>standing up stiffly,  she<br>lays her art out to dry. <br>then she leaves the room<br>with a satisfied sigh. <br>the worldâ’s breath is drawn;<br>every creature is waiting. <br>newborn sunbeams shine<br>down on the painting. <br>what she had waited for, <br>and used a brush to express, <br>is exposed to allâ—<br>no more,  no less. <br>there,  basking in daylight, <br>still damp in the heat of june, <br>pearled with a glow of its own, <br>is an alabaster full moon.

title: War and Peace

text: the chariot of death went up the sreet,  picking up passengers amidst screams,  some wanted to come,  some did not,  some sat quietly,  some told stories of their deaths.  every story was the same.  the spirit of war came,  and took them away.  every mind,  every soul said the same prayer.  when would the dove of peace come? when would the sun rise? when would mother earth be free of this ordeal?  then as the world was about to end.  the dove of peace soared above the sky.  the war was over.  finally mother earth was free of the terrible ordeal.  every soul looked around for their kith and kin,  but where were they? the chariot of death was carrying them away.

title: Broken girl
author: zoha
text: she loved a boy who loved her too,  it was only because their love was new.  she loved him with all her heart,  one day that heart broke apart.  it all end that day he said,  finish im gone.   she thought theres something wrong.   she asked are u alright few seconds passed he started to fight.   she was shocked her heart was locked.   the key he had but now he was mad.   hes all she needs,  and hes the one her heart leads.  he was too selfish and never realized that he was hurtingâ  her.  his words didnt say anything but his actions were breaking her.   she cried and cried every night coz that person wasnt right.  she fell so hard that forgot the cause,  loved him breaking the laws.  no one was there to give her shoulder,  every night became colder and colder.   all those messages were a lie,  she thought this and started to cry.    all those memories she remember,  that ended in november.   someone took her place,  she wanted to race,  to get back that face.  those pictures they took,  cant believe what they look.   two angels sent from above to shower each other with love.   her life was a miracle,  but now her situation was critical.   she had no idea what to do,  no one knew what she was going through.    she took too much stress and got very depressed.   all she thinks about are the times they spent together,  she believed they would be together forever.   hes happy with his new life,  but doesnt care how she would survive.   he hugged her as if shes his world,  but who knew that she wasn't the only girl.  she loved him so much that forgot the pain.  that night it rained,  her wrists were stained.    whole night she was thinking that will he go? she thought and thought and then he said no.  she was shivering in happiness coz she believed,  she was so happy that all her pain relieved.   he told her i love u she said too.  then later he said,  its not for u.   she pinched herself thinking its a dream,  but when she knew its true she started to scream.   as they walked under the sun he gave her shade,  that was the only thing for what he was made.   but then it was too late all those memories fade.   days passed by,  she asked why.   what did she do,  hope someone loves her too.   she had no choice,  but just to accept that voice.   which said u r finished everything is over,  killing her from inside slower and slower.   she couldn't believe what was going on,  all she wanted to do was hold on.   to those unforgettable memories,  heart races,  that reminds her of those two happy faces.    one day she found him sitting on a hill,  what she saw made her stand still.   his wrists were bleedingâ  fully red,  for sometime she thought hes gone mad. â   she sat beside him wanted to know,  something deep that he couldn't show.  his eyes bursted out of tears,  but to say he had some fear.   she thought this time he wont leave her,  but he proved her wrong.   she tried to move on,  but she was no more strong.   whenever she looks at the stars she remember her scars.   she deserved better,  but got him.   now its over and she lost him .

title: Where to begin?
author: aaron
text: where words dictate the only choice for fantasies,  is where an ending awaits a new beginning.  that's how an image can draw itself: with the tools necessary.  and some poems need more: we call them dreamers.  to dream is not to be,  a character's image.  to paint off the page is to finish the impossible,  but within the frame is only the possibility of what can be understood.  no word can draw what a feeling has no words for,  but to acknowledge that the feelings can see outside the frame.  sentences need a period to find satisfaction,  and will find those without it to lack something.  this lack,  or fragment of a completed sentence,  that lacks an expression's satisfaction,  is the only capable cure for an otherwise square reality.  after the cure comes the hard part: there's no hard part in dreaming about a square reality.  then the poem finds a difficulty in creating its own language.  and this is where the poem begins. .

text: i am from dark nights from sadness and unhappy light i am from living with my grandparents to our apartment  i am from the happy daffodils from the japanese maple the soil turning through  our fingers  i am from blood shot eyes from a father who was never there iâ’m from hard work and living on a college campus from never really being alone  iâ’m from be quiet and donâ’t tell anyone and this isnâ’t that bad iâ’m from a dream world,  a never ending loop iâ’m from dread.  from my mom having a boyfriend  in 2006 iâ’m from the box of letters sitting under my bed left unsent.

title: An Unsavable Girl

text: somebody has to go polish the stars as they tarnish night in and night out  what once was new is now all used  who wants to gaze  at the dull sparkle when there is plenty new  somebody has to polish the stars show them they are not forgotten show them they too are a view  the tarnished stars sparkle  on the darkest nights as they wait  to be polished  somebody has to polish the stars for the skies blanket is getting rather lonely as they leave one by one only leaving behind scars  polish the stars i beg you they deserve to be happy too for they are special   polish the stars somebody has to why not you?

title: One Fall Evening
author: adrienne
text: bitter cold fall air rung with electric laughter the song of birds everyday life the crunching of crimson leaves the nonstop,  almost rhythmic,  chatter   the sky almost cloudless highlighted the bare trees the bitter fall wind has nothing to wrestle with as the leaves are gone  an imaginary world i long left behind illuminated his features  the world where grendel existed and beowulf could defeat him  he waits with anticipation thinking about who will win is she going to beat him? he thinks with rosey red cheeks   a tortured wail as you see head over heal and slam momentary silence hearts are off beat the rest of the way is  silent.

title: Our Youth
author: alajiah
text: the aroma of dust and dirt,  filling our noses without distraction.  we jump,  dance,  laugh,  without a care each of us filled with energy; action.  we were never alone,  or scared.   the flowers scrubbing our ankles,  tickling us with their fleecy leaves and stems.  grass like a pillow and feather,  the birds and animalsâ’ delightful hymns.  we were happy,  no tears,  no pain.   our youth is fading like dry tears,  it is a bird flying away,  soaring.  our minds are sinking into black,  here come the attitudes of minds roaring.  happiness is fading; more tears.   we are now pushed into leadership.  mind is a light past,  and distant future forced into labor,  into love; death.  thereâ’s no way back,  unless we find a cure.  if we find happiness,  weâ’re youth.

title: Start Over
author: alex
text: glasses on ,  tools nearby,  prepared.  two pieces of wood,  simple task,   much more than expected at first.  90 degrees they stand together,  tape,  double sided like a coin,   everywhere.  everything attached with ease,  except for the motor controllers that is.   four old ones,  two new,  they taunt me.   red screws,  and black screws i've seen,  but now there's green and white too? everything is on my table,   but hidden at the same time wire strippers leave casings strewn about.  something smells suspicious,  hopefully not lithium.  yep.  itâ’s lithium.  after the battery is gone,  i continue.   everything looks like it's connected right,  so i test my board.  it doesn't work so i try the wires again.  bad crimp there.   start over.  i try again.  wires too tight.  start over.  broken wire.  start over.  i think i finally have it! and i do!  but someone robs me of my motor controllers.  useless now.  start over.

title: The fight for life
author: alex
text: no matter what i do   no matter where i go   i leave a path of wreckage behind me   that no one can seem to get through.    i try to be gentle   i try to be careful   but every time i show up   everything drops to a lower level.    i'm neither a jewel nor a gem   not a treasure nor a coal    but if i'm not that then what am i?   just an empty body with no soul. .    i walk this earth   in a daze,  in a coma   going through just day by day   smelling life's dead aroma.    no way out   no exit sign   trapped in the game   stuck in this head of mine.

title: A Drowning City
author: alexandra
text: as the snow settles  on the city grounds,  itâ’s abruptly awaken by  a shake.      \t\t\t\t\t    a quiver.                \t\t\t\t\ta quake.   thousands of white crystals  float around the glorious scene,  and leisurely descend to the grounds once more,   a blanket of happiness,  a moment of magic,  slowly destroyed in seconds.   the people are frightened,  the city is calm.  everything is ordinary again.   a whole white world inside a globe of pure glass,  upon an embellished base,   sitting on an old,   rustic,  wooden high rise,  sparkling like a pair  of sapphire blue eyes.   the set of globes  becoming dull,  are coated in  \tgrime.  \t         filth.                               smut.   memories from a  childhood's past a collection that will always last.

title: Memories

title: Inquiry
author: alexandra
text: the average 4-year-old asks 437 questions a day.    437 questions  everyday   a child lives  with their mind  cracked open  free to every thought whim fantasy  how many questions did you ask today?  what kind of questions were they?  what time is it?  what's the temperature outside?  mundane  boring  questions   children ask questions that stretch the boundaries  of human knowledge  they ponder things adults wouldn't dare to   they dream things beyond  imaginative limits   a four-year-old will ask â â â â what is this? for they are not afraid  of being judged for ignorance  a four-year-old will ask  â â â â â why? for they see life with the lense of curiosity  a four-year-old asks 437 questions everyday
