title: Tree of Life
author: alexis
text: i hear the ringing of the charms.  i see the happiness displayed on my motherâ’s face.    a big celebration,  joy is radiating.  the life of the little man being housed by another human,  is finally beginning.  my fatherâ’s life now continues to bloom,  like a flower in the spring.  he was in chains for so long,  being held back from things he loves.  almost as if he was a prisoner.  fight after fight,  he was finally free.  once he was free,  a celebration was needed.   the bracelet was the circle of life,  while the charm was the tree of life.  a celebration of new life,  and old life continued.

title: His Imperfections
author: alexis
text: his eyes were the deep green of the fields we frolic in,   brown,  like the dampened soil of the ground,   dark blue,  like the sky and oceans that surrounds us.  though one seemed more field than soil,   his earthly,  hazel eyes were unique,  one slightly smaller than the other.  his smile was that of deep thought,  the way it curved and creased when the corners were turned up.  the way the dip in his lip had a story to tell.   his face was that of perfect imperfections.  everything that was a flaw,  was what made him worth it.  worth the love that has filled my heart.  his hair that brown color,  that without proper knowledge would seem boring,  but if you know,  holds the sun in its certain strands.  his face,  his eyes,  his smile,  there has a story to tell,  in every aspect of his body,  he had a mark that told a tale.  his was one that i wanted to learn.  a fairy-tale prince charming worth reading about,  let us learn this story of the world and love.

title: Seasons
author: alexis
text: in the winter i miss my flip flops and short shorts.  i miss sun tanning and diving into the waves on the beach.  feeling the wind run through my hair,  stress free life.   in the spring i miss when it didnâ’t rain so much.  when i didnâ’t have to carry around a pouch of tissues everywhere i go.   and when bees didnâ’t threaten to sting me  and bugs stayed out of my eyes.   in the summer i miss the pure white snow and the joy of christmas.  i miss not feeling the sweat condensed down my forehead.  and my hair not being frizzy and nappy in the humidity  in the fall i miss jumping in the pool and no school.  iâ’d take back the warmer weather in an instant.  i miss the sunshine and long nights,  the vibrant green grass and pretty colors of the flowers.   the seasons come and go.   like fire burning paper to ashes their gone before you know.

title: Have You?
author: alix
text: have you ever seen a sunrise? stretching its arms across the bleak horizon painting the world with its colors  beautifully blinding.   have you ever heard a sunrise? inviting you into the fiery abyss drawing you near silent visions to the eye.   have you ever smelt a sunrise? citrus scent of a sweet summer drink wafting through the air gradually getting stronger until it is no more.   have you ever tasted a sunrise? allowing the warmness to slide down; letting it sink permitting the butterflies to arise.  stickly sweet.   have you ever held a sunrise? bestowing you with such power an immense numbness  lasting only moments  gone as it goes,  fading into days.

title: Icarus
author: allison
text: leave the door open just a crack let some light in here want to see the pictures on my walls want to see their shadows blossom want to see their faces distort want to let my imagination break my chains and run frenetic through this room and through this world and through the sky and through this life unfettered! at last… crumpled,  scattered clothes and papers (crumpled,  scattered feathers drifting…) crumpled,  scattered dreams dissipate (across the baleful blue…) into vivid,  vibrant,  valiant,  victorious chimeras (and down to earth…) of uncharted opportunity (before the sun could set…) fail me never! fail me not! fail me if my life is bought… but only if the price is fairer still than the shimmering face i feel you sparkle like a diamond when i think iâ’ve lost the stars you lift me on feathers of silk,  dear icarus that dare not melt beneath the scolding sun oh,  send me where you will,  my love for i will surely fly without the hindrance of those leaden fingers on my spine look into the sun! look into the beckoning blue! look into the beautiful eyes of life! it calls you so… fly! this is your chance,  lovely fowl this is your zephyr; let it take you where it will away from your feet away from your head away from your hands away from your anchor away from your waxen,  lifeless,  laughable figurines they melt beneath the sun.  but you? dear icarus,  you have feathers of silk (a skeleton of wax…) you sparkle like lost stars (i wish you everlasting flight…) you alone can escape the labyrinth! (dear icarus…!) for the sake of sanity… (your feathers cloud my eyes…) fly! (from the sun. ) and may my shadow never guide you home.

title: Flight of the Phoenix
author: allison
text: a little bit of temperament  within a mighty shell of laborious incompetence you donâ’t know me very well  social butterfly with a gimp introvert with a flair please disregard my evident limp while iâ’m soaring through the air  one hand dances over crystalline keys one hand creates shadow and light one eye sees the path right in front of me while the other gauges my flight  i have wings so broad they could sweep the clouds i have feet so fast they can flee my own wrath i have eyes so sharp i can see through your shroud and decipher your alien epitaph  all for one,  and one for me iâ’m only climbing so i can feel free i know thatâ’s where youâ’d rather be but if you could,  please believe in me  and if i fall into depths below wings crippled and eyes struck blind i want no more than simply to know you wish you were falling at my side.

title: Mosquitoes
author: alpona
text: mosquitoes,  so many of them! proboscis as tough as stem.  better call them by their scientific name- culicidae one enough to spoil somebody's day! a perfect spoilsport indeed,  which can survive in weed or reed.  culex,  anopheles,  aedes- so many! found especially in the rainy.  be cognizant,  there are many more mansonia,  kimiya,  malaya are some of the famous four.  you can count out more of vices than virtues,  one direct sting would let you loose.  male anopheles is vegan as he feeds on leaves,  females are non- vegetarian as she bites a tuck off sleeve! they are cumbersome,  burdensome,  troublesome oh! i am too vexed to think of all synonyms to come! god,  i encountered with a mosquito again as i sat down to relieve myself of the pain.  one sting would be miniscule frequent repetitions on my face would make me look like a mule.  pray,  stop this beast to let me doze off this night at least!

title: The Misty Path
author: alyssa
text: the path is long and narrow as it goes beyond the gates,  through the forests full of evergreens.  i pause,  as i meditate.  on the signs of new life,  a reminder to us of our risen christ.  the path stops at the edge of a stream,  as do we stop when we're confused and tangled up in life.  for we should not fear,  god is on our side.  the other side is like a bad reflection we don't want to see.  so i stop at the end of the misty path by the stream,  and pray a short prayer,  for i am thankful i am on this side.

title: One Small Fist
author: alyssa
text: clenching and opening one small hand, â” knowing i wonâ’t die today.  a whole life is ahead of me,  15 years young,  still going strong from every push and pull.  every moment from the past playing a large role on who i am today.  the things that i remember,  things i donâ’t all had a tiny effect that transformed to a large one.  as i still live on i know i want to make an impact,  make an impact on myself,  make an impact on others,  and on the world.  knowing this makes me live my life as interesting and exciting as possible.  with this,  i won't die today still leaving my hand in a small fist.

title: Dream
author: amanda
text: ever rest your head down to sleep,  close you eyes and it's me you dream,  trying to escapes life and what it seems to be,  obstacles too plain to see,  trying to escape life humanity,  i try my hardest to be by your side,  , i understand what you feel but you can't hide,  give me a chance to you i'd be true never lie,  i know who you are just under the skin.  got to work what is thrown at you but bleeding within,  i've given you signs,  hints the whole nine,  so can't tell me i'm not trying,  i don't know what you see or think in your mind,  got to dig deeper inside to see what i find,  i pull out a note addressed to me,  i open it up and try to read what i see,  but than i wake up,  still reaching for you,  following my heart but my mind has no clue,  my dreams are to escape my life,  during that time you take all my strife,  so please don't wake me from my wonder world,  that's when i dream i'm your perfect girl,  and i know deep down inside you like it too

title: The Best Brother
author: amanda
text: i never knew how much i loved you until now,  when i'm about to lose you.  we've been through so much stuff together i see now i don't want you to go,  not ever.  i have treated you so bad for so long.  when all you did was love me,  all the days long now you want to go to the military and i want to tell you,  life will be scary i can't look at your picture without crying,  even though i keep trying and trying.  i'm going to miss the way you grin and the way you wrote your name in pen i'm going to miss your sense of humor and forget your voice,  i hope it'll murmur.  i'm going to forget the way you hug me.  the way you held me tight,  and loved me.  i'm going to miss all the good times we've had and regret how i wasted all the good times with bad.  there are so many things about you i'll miss.  i wish you would have never thought of this you have loved me and shown me compassion and hugged me with hugs of love your hugs are what i love most because your hugs showed me how much you care.  i love you forever and ever,   and don't want you to leave,  not ever.

title: It Would Be So Wonderful
author: amanda
text: it would be so wonderful if you were the one for me.   if your eyes were the ones i was born to look into and see my future.   if your voice was the one i was made to hear and listen to my life.   if your lips were the ones i was created to kiss and every time get tingles in my soul.   if your body was the one i was ment to caress and hold at night while we protect each other from our nightmares and our fears simply by that touch.   if you,  yourself was the one i'm destined to love forever,  the other half of me,  myself.   wouldn't it be wonderful?

title: Another Day

title: A Good Friend
author: amanda
text: to me you are a good friend,  and i'll be here for you,  from now until the end.  there's nothing i won't do for you,  there's no risk i won't take,  and i want you to know my love is not fake.  i love the time we spend together,  and i will be a good friend to you,  from now until forever.  i love you with all my heart,  i knew we'd be good friends from the start.  i miss you when we are apart,  i dream of you when i sleep,  i love talking to you night or day,  you always know what to say,  even if you're a thousand miles away.  i want to thank you for being such a good friend,  and i want you to see,  that for you,  right here is where i'll be.

title: Band
author: amanda
text: this morning i woke up,  i got up,  got dressed.  i finished my homework,  brushed my teeth,  and put on my brand new plaid vest.  i went through the day without cracking a smile.  then it was the end of the day,  6th period.  this ment band had come without delay.  as i walked to vallhala,  i couldn't stand the wait.  i got to the classroom,  and got my saxophone.  i put it together,  and set down the pleather case.  then started to put together the bass,  clarinet.  we started to play our first song with haste,  and played it without a mistake.  after that we played gladiator,  and i played my angry squeaks of repetative anger.  this one hour a day is what i live for,  its what i eat,  its what i drink,  its what i breath,  its what i sleep.

title: Untitled
author: anastasia
text: it is not the traces of love that drives us to tears of hopelessness,  it is the placid void that follows what once was.   it is not the inconspicuous hatred that keeps us going,  it is the need for passion that takes us away from destitution.   it is not the ever-lasting attention that teaches us to treasure,  it is  the familiarity with desolation that enables us to appreciate affection.   it is not the dependancy on others that allows us to stand alone,  it is the faith in ourselves that brings us together.

title: One Man
author: anastasia
text: i can feel him in the distance fighting for his own existence; his muscles taut by windswept rain,   strength of dragon,  grace of crane.   a warrior stands alone,  even in a crowd in perpetual silence,  of lives heâ’d shroud; only the foolish would make the mistake,   stealth of leopard,  flexibility of snake.   his secrets kept hidden,  his battle cry- a look at his victims,  he lets out a sigh; threat overcome,  heâ’s neither seen nor heard,   respected as tiger,  humble as bird.

title: The King of Jalepigong's Nose
author: andrea
text:
let's all go to jalepigong.
it is a wonderful place.
the people sing a lot of songs
about the things on their face.
why, i once heard one long
about the great face disgrace
when the king's nose went wrong
for he hit it on his mace
and so the kingdom went along
with the face misplace
of the king, but the song went on
to tell of the great vase
that fell (you guessed it), right upon
the good king's face!
let's all go to jalepigong
for it is a wonderful place
let us remember time foregone
and let the king keep his place.
with his straight nose on
his face!

text: basketball is a game that we love  something we always think of  winning is what we desire  but not every athlete can acquire  in this game we can be a model  that someday every kid will follow  obstacles in the way can be a challenge  but we are not afraid since we can manage  as we drive to the center  we cant be scared of the defender  loosing may bring a tear  but crying will show our fear  we have a lot of determination  this is what we need in every situation  practice is what we do every day  this will makes us stronger someday  we run back and forth  from both ends of the floor  this can be tiring  but its worth it when you're trying  failure is not an option  triumph is our function  coordination at it's best  brings players to a test  a fade away is what we invest  but creativity is seen by the rest  dribbling may be a challenge  but shooting is our talent  we will do anything to win  until the last sweat runs through our skin  weakness leaving the body is called pain  without it we have no game  there will be times when we suffer  but only this can make us tougher  basketball is the best  disagreement can come from the rest  many would try  but few will shine

title: Wasteland
author: angilique
text: maybe i'm a different breed,  maybe i'm the mystery,   locked up in your head,   at night when you are in your bed,  those thoughts you can't bare,   with the ones who wouldn't care,  the more you smile the more they frown    can't make the mile  only going down  maybe i'm a different breed  but it's not a mystery can't breath  can't speak  all i know is my name is angilique love with many definitions  warped in many positions  broken before i hit the ground  will you ever come around dreams of the future  slowly coming true  inferred thoughts of insanity   no point of profanity  born with alcohol in thy blood  judgment beginning to flood  skin and bones appearing in the mirror  swearing it's lies,  now you are inferior  i know i'm a different breed  more then just mysteries  yearning to feed  on my soulless needs under my skin  rotten and caving in  constantly feeling used  forgetting the pain of abuse  watching life fade  knowing we were never meant to be made  there is more behind this name angilique  you may say it's unique  but it's more common the you think  it's in your reflection as you begin to sink  pen and paper become a refuge  even though technology became huge  split into categories of two  individuality was made for who sleeping is a necessity  when sadness becomes prosperity  6 o'clock became my warden  another pill for my personal burden medication for every emotion causing only more commotion  human robots soon to be an epidemic mindless zombie sounds more realistic my secrets are bursting at the seams  ready for my blood curdling screams  silent rendezvous  from myself to you  growing in the shadows of a dead man  hoping to be like him in all the ways i  can  young body with an old soul  flames grasping at each coal  eternal war in my heart  a defined laser will soon tear it apart  this deck of cards is now my fate  being dealt,  anticipating the wait  priority becomes appearance  now obtaining a low coherence  promises never kept thoughts that society will never accept  friends are now secret enemies  waking up with suicidal fantasies  ouch just said something deep  that drugs can't defeat  don't be upset  don't lose my beat  place me back in your basket  remember we are playing for keeps read this once,  twice,  even thrice  in the end shame is sure the price  understand,  i hope not  you are just a problem in my plot  yearning to fly  well so am i  money is the only greed  in this game of want and need  becoming my pawn  as you all read along  confusion is my story  i'll warn you it's kind of gory  12 hour labor  couldn't be later  my life was intended to be heaven  on march 22,  1997 love and possibilities in my first 4 years of life  ruptured by a shotgun that gave my father the short end of the knife  in 6 months baby brother on the way  praying mommy won't go away  months on end  always alone  no time to spend  hunger pains stabbed through each bone  memories of needles,  cuts,  and bruises hearing all of those screaming refusals  living in every state  with no place to salvate  many attempted to replace my father  but inside i know there is no other  many schools,  many friends  even though i never fit in  bad decisions  no consequences stop the screaming before she gets mad  or your living hell will turn bad  go to mommy for comfort as she pulls out a knife  her cuts run deep as she begins to slice  police at the door  need i say more  in a few weeks she will return  this fire inside me continues to burn  barely raised but can determine between right and wrong   watching people in your house hit from a bong  seeing the needle penetrate mommy's arm  telling yourself you will never do such self harm  teaching your brother all you know  hoping it will help him grow  growing up he remained untouched  with a minor incident he was screwed  i feel guilt and shame  for not protecting him when the time came  reached out in faith and hope  as family jumped that rope  many offered to take us in  while mommy was in the pen  i exploded with truth which got us away  thankful i am that we no longer live that way  but the ways of my mother is all my brother knew  he found her exciting even after all he's been through  this story of mine is the same as millions   even though i am one in six billion  angilique is just a name  in the worlds failure of fame  do you see me in a different view  now that i have just begun to spew i may just be a different breed  we just pulled a layer off my mystery

title: Awaken to a Dream
author: austin
text: the snowflakes fall upon the ground; i see the glint of light,  every turn the crystals take,  the glass provokes my sight.  i pause in silence,  take a breath,  and rest a moment there,  the feather-like faintly falling flakes like mirrors in the air.   i nod my head in satisfaction,  a mystery there beheld,  t'was a beauty in that animation my soul had then instilled the trees rocked back and forth,  within the wind: a lullaby,  together swaying gently like a chorus on the sky.   the sunbeams bounce off miles of snow and on my back they rest,  a smile appears and that warm feeling spreads throughout my chest.  awed at this scene,  so picturesque,  peace gently filled my eyes,  a peace that spills through valleys deep,  like beams upon sunrise.   the brilliant sun is in its prime and tilting my head to the sky,  i gaze in dreamy inspiration,  and speechless,  my reply.  it takes a second glance to see the fragile sky,  en route,  ever slowly sliding,  in its airy institute.   movement almost non-existent even when i stare,  floating,  rolling,  gliding gently on a makeshift bed of air.  clouds of cotton candy white are painted on this canvas in bouquets,  these raining never-ending prisms now are winter's fiancã©s.   i lay and think and soak up all that nature had to say,  and the stress that overcame me had been quickly stripped away.  as i lay engulfed in feeling,  comforted in natures lap,  i start to doze under a tree fulfilled as i wake from my nap.

text: the sun looked through the dark clouds,  trying to shine.  there was a wind howling in the distance,  almost saying â“donâ’t try iâ’m to strong for youâ”.  but the sun wouldnâ’t give; it tried to force itself through the dark clouds,  pushing and pulling at them,  and then all of a sudden it was quiet,  the sun looked puzzled,  and all the clouds moved for the sun,  like they were being pushed by something that wasnâ’t there.   the world wanted the sun to shine,  to bring joy and warmth to the faces of every race to bring hope,  happiness and joy,  to the young,  old,  and the teens of the world.  the world wanted the sun to bring hope to many  and thatâ’s exactly how the sun brought hope to many,  because the world deserved happiness.

text:
as i look up to the cloudless sky, just telling myself how good life is, there is only one thought that circles around my head, iâ’m just lucky to have met you, iâ’m so lucky to have crossed paths with you, being apart of your life has made mine better, now youâ’ve become apart of me, apart of me that i canâ’t live without, apart of me that is missing every time youâ’re not around, . . you really have no idea how much i care about you, you really have no idea how much i love you, . . but sometimes life takes a tumble, things get difficult for everyone, but the one thing i will always do, is care about you, and, love you for who you really are, and iâ’ll always be there for you, if there was only one part you that i could cherish forever, iâ’d have apart of your heart, if i had that iâ’d have the universe, because that would be everything iâ’d need, apart of your heart, to help me through everything, like you help me through everything, writing this now, reminds me of how much i appreciate you, how much i care, how much you mean to me,

the world is good place to be, but if i could have you, iâ’d never want to leave.

title: Our Friendship:
author: breanna
text: our friendship means the world to me,  without it the sun wouldnâ’t shine,  the world would be gloomy,  every time youâ’re around i feel so alive,  you bring true happiness to me,  you mean the world to me,  and when youâ’re around you make feel strong,  and this inner confidence and passion bursts out of me,  like a colourful jack in the box.  with a friendship so strong,  like a wall made of concrete.  with two strong hearts melted together as one,   and a special friendship that is life long.  iâ’m so glad to have been best-friends with you.  iâ’ll never forget your kind heart,  and words of wisdom.  iâ’ll never forget the one that inspired me to be great.  iâ’ll never forget our special friendship.

title: Life:
author: breanna
text: as she started to cry,  a tear fell as blue as the ocean,  fell from her eye,  gently rolling down her silky skin,  careful not to bruise its perfection,  it gently touched her cheek,  and crept around her lips,   she reached out,  catching the tear,  catching its innocence and passion; she smiled with inspiration in her eyes,  the tear soaked into her skin,   travelling around her whole body,  filling her with hope and happiness,   her body began to shudder; her mind began to spring into life,  she gazed into the blue cloudless sky,  breathing in all the life surrounding her body,  feeling the air with her soft finger tips,  closing her eyes,  feeling the sun crispin her skin,   she sat down,  touching every strand of grass she could grasp,  feeling the life inside them,  watching a lady bird crawl over her hand,  then blissfully flying away,   there was only one thought in her mind,  life is great!

title: A shift in my heart:
author: breanna
text: a shift in my heart:    this morning i woke,  with hope in my heart,  i waited and waited,  for you to come through the door,  you never did,  although my heart still in pain,  cries for you everyday,  the hope starts to fade,   a shift in my heart,  has begun,  moving forward,  searching for the caller of my heart,  the angel in my heart,   will always be you,   my heart has cried,  long enough,  iâ’ve been waiting to long,   always know that you have the key,  the key to my heart,  be careful,  cherish the key,  itâ’s a symbol of the best thing in my life,  it is a symbol of my love,  for you,  donâ’t forget it,  as i wont forget you,   the shift has begun,  a shift in my heart,  searching for the one,  how i wish it was you. . .

title: Space:
author: breanna
text: space:   the clock ticked by,  the time flying,  the undeniable space,  she just wanted to be alone,  no rules,  no hurt,  she wanted space,  to figure out herself,  to figure out everything,  why did she feel this way? to feel good about herself,  to feel the life around her,  to find another love,  find another angel,  she could tell everything,  spill her heart to,  feel loved,  just being who she is,  that where she wants to be,  in a place where nothing hurts,  she can go wherever she likes,  just being herself,  with someone who loves her,  for who she is. . .

title: Little wonders:
author: breanna
text: little wonders:    the little wonders,  circle around my head,  why do these things happen? what does life have planned for me? for everyone,   where has the curiosity gone? what happened to inner belief? these little wonders,  twists and turns of fate,  make us,   who we are,  help us believe,  the things we believe in,   for ourselves,  life is precious,  everything happens for a reason,  the reason are never understood,  but we still believe.

title: Belle:
author: breanna
text: belle:     belle,  youâ’re so beautiful,  we connected as soon as our eyes met,  i started seeing you in my dreams.  you treated me like an angel,  always hugging me,  telling me you care,  i really want to meet you one day belle,  i really want to be with you,  i really wish your kisses werenâ’t just a part of my dreams,  i really wish i could show you the affection you show me,  i owe you everything,  you helped me move on,  to better things,  youâ’ve always been there for me,  comforting,  complementing,  being everything,  by just being you,  a beautiful angel,  that has the biggest heart in the world,  it was love at first sight,  iâ’ll see you soon,  in my dreams,  dear belle,  i love you,  with everything,  just how you love me,  you always have,  been my girl forever.

title: The End:
author: breanna
text: the end:   the end begun,  with a dark cloud,  pouring rain,  raging anger,  it ended in a second,  i canâ’t hurt you anymore,  our friendship was great,  the best,  but it ended ages ago,  we just kept holding on,  itâ’s for the best,  you have everything now,  a great life to live,  leave me behind,  where i left you,  too much has happened,  too much pain and hurt has shed,  you were the best friend i ever had,  it just didnâ’t work,  time wasnâ’t on our side,  we grew apart,  this is what life wants,  this is our path,  apart,  this is the end.

title: Zooming Through Life
author: briana
text: dear life,   i have chosen to zoom through you.  for the conclusion i have not come to.  people have hurt me and you've seen that.  it's a sudden sorrow as a matter of fact.  you've seen faces come and go.  too many to count,  too many to know.  scars hidden beneath my clothes.  this is the path that i so gratefully chose.  the laughter came and then it left.  leaving me with nights with no rest.  you can say the tears came with an ease.  leaving me with a please.  so i have chosen to leave this life as fast as i can.  leaving behind every memory,  every man.  i'll do it quick,  like a walk in the park.  i guess this journey was too much to embark.  some will miss me and some will not.  but know it was my love that he caught.  he meant more to me than anything.  maybe that's why,  this life,  i'm leaving.  for i cannot be with him as long as i want.  because it's my heart he doesn't want to flaunt.  they say it's a stupid reason to die.  but he was more than just

title: My Love For You

text: from the depths of my heart,  to the earth's core.  you are my one true love,  who i could love for ever more.   in my mind you will always be,  and in my heart is where you will stay.  if i did not know you,  i could not live another day.   from the bottom of the deepest ocean,  to the top of the highest mountain.  my love for you  is like a fountain.   for you i would love,   and i would cry.  but most of all,   for you i would die.

title: I Don't Want You
author: britney
text: you wander why i don't want you.  when you lie,  decieve do whatever you can  to get what you want.  you act like you're the best like i should feel lucky just to be with you.  and you wander why i don't want you.  you parade around like an egotistic peacock,  smiling at only the ''select'' few that you feel deserve your attention.  and you wander why i don't want you.  so the next time you're racking your brains trying to come up with a reason,  think about your actions,  about all the hearts you've broken about all the people you've hurt all the egos you've crushed.  and figure out why i don't want you.

title: ''Bench Warmer''
author: bryce
text: i'm sitting on the bench of life,  watching it all go by,  no significance to others,  just a bench warmer.  i'm expendable,  used until i'm no longer needed,  a replacement.  my heart is no longer in the game,  i've been gone for quite awhile,  but when will you notice? i'm not the me i used to be,  the happy,  cheery me.  i've been gone for quite awhile,  you haven't noticed,  but i'm not me.  my faith is gone,  my beliefs crumbled,  i don't know what to think,  i don't know what to do,  all i can do is try and survive.  i'm helping you find your home,  when i've been lost for quite awhile,  don't know where to go,  waiting for life to go.  i'm sitting on the bench of life,  watching it all go by,  and i've noticed this one thing. . .  i'm all alone.

title: It's Warmer Up the Hill
author: bryn
text: the sun beckoned me up through the close knit trees      on a narrow trail           to see the golden field.  up on the hill the grass was pressed down      green           tangled                grabbing my feet begging me to stay and sit like those who had before me.  butterflies fluttered around the peaks of      orange           purple                flowers.  nothing could possibly capture what i was      seeing           feeling.  nothing could capture      the sun            beating down causing sweat to build  on the back of my neck.       the webs            tickling my arms invisible and without a host.       winged bugs           zipping around as if there were somewhere  they needed to be.       red beetles            crawling up                 and down stems i tried to avoid.  nothing      could possibly capture           how the golden sun                made the golden field                     glow.

title: You Left Without Saying Good Bye
author: cassandra
text: you left when i was in need you left without saying good bye.  how am i to think of you? you ask why i hate you,  haven't you figured it out? you left and didn't come back.  how do you think i felt? all alone with no mom thinking its all my fault.  left with my baby sister  to raise with out a mother.   you left without saying good bye.   now you want me back? you lost your chance 16 years ago you are out of my life,  you made your choice,  and it was to leave without saying good bye.  i will always love you  no matter what,  you count on that,  but now its my time to step up,  and say good bye.

title: The Oracle's Counsel
author: cassandra
text: the days fly by like hunted birds.  time tries to spite me by racing my voice as my words struggle to escape my throat before death is their keeper.  the sing-song ticks of the clock echo between the spaces in my head and remind me that few listen.  i can taste time pass in my tea;the flavor is dull.  the black mug that once warmed my hands now chills them.  before my eyes,  i watch an entire generation make each mistake i had during my youth.  i can feel the sting of each knife as it penetrates their turned backs,  and i can taste the blood in their sassy mouths each time they must bite their tongues.  secretive insanity pokes and prods the boring and inexplicable fact of life.  the same way einstein poked and prodded the dumb logic of math back in his days.  that logic wasn't that dumb.  the porcelain dreams of babies stay behind their welded  lips and encased within their glass thoughts.  but the beats from the street are pounded into your head like a brain is drum,  and rhythm are sticks.  because the people who want to be heard have no other way of speaking their minds except to scream it out.  have i told you how good it feels to be me? only because i can see tomorrow.  the tattered leashes of our brains will break soon.  not even the brain of the psych ward patient in the padded pink room is running amuck compared to the way ours will.  the world will spin backwards and sing songs of mercy and anti-war.  cat's claws won't be gentle anymore.  she is going to dig them deep into the flesh of sleepers.  plastic emotions will be thrown out the window of care.  everyone who was once loved will be forgotten.  and as each final tick from the clock of doom echoes between the walls of this cage that we are nothing but birds too,

title: Blithe Berceuse
author: caydalin
text: in the eyes of the lord i am but a candlelight among millions.  there is no pleasure among those who dwell in the dark,  only greed,  violence,  and sorrow.  it is wise to think of us as a tiny fragment of a whole.  every little piece is very crucial in the idea of creating something more than what we are as humans.  we are in-debt to no one,  yet with one simple exception.  life,  we essentially live out our choices and our faults.  although,  who are we to hate those who know only love.  we become hateful jealous souls lost in obscurity.  yet the world is full of souls who do not know the love of god and never will until someone teaches them his grace.  only then will these lost souls change.  it is never too late to adore the man upstairs.         i donâ’t know how i became what i am,  but there sure are a couple ideas that come to mind.  maybe i give too much because. . . well because,  i know what it feels like to be hungry and having almost nothing.  poverty goes on all over the globe with remarkable help.  there are a large amount of individuals in this world who would give to the helpless without a second glance.  i should be greedy,  holding on to what i gain and control.  i should be resembling scrooge or something close to that.  everything that is said and done does not change the fact that i always believed i was born to change the lives of those around me in a simply virtuous nature.         i love people.  i feel what those near me feel sometimes.  helping people really does take a toll on our personal lives,  but it can be rewarding.  personal details about who i am is not the reason why i write. . . or type.  i write because iâ’ve always wanted to thank those who were and exist in my life now.  i am only sixteen,  but as a sixteen year old i have truly gone through a troublesome of a lot.  i am still making up great times to cover all the negative scraps.

title: It's So  Wrong

title: Wishing On A Star
author: chelsea
text: at night when everyone is asleep,  the streets are so empty,  the neighborhood is so quiet.  no one makes a peep.  the sky is dark black with a full moon and the clouds hugging it.   the stars are out tonight,  lighting up the sky.  everything looks so peaceful.  everything seems so calm.  i wish you were here to see it.

title: It doesn't have a title
author: chelsea
text: as i sit here completly zoned,  only one thing runs through my mind.  i can only think how i let you down,  and how you've changed.  i say i'm a space cadet,  you simpily laugh.  wanting to cry i manage a smile,  even though inside i'm torn in two.  told smiling was the right thing to do,  i'm even more confused.  why must the rightthing hurt so much,  and will it end? it feels weird to talk to you,  i can no longer hug you.  now i must bare your troubles and mine,  not wanting to hurt anyone the way i did you.  in saying this i'm sure,  my words have hurt another soul.  sorry those who wish to help,  i don't want you to end up like me.  yet thanx to you i live on,  or am i alive?

title: Finally
author: chelsea
text: we became distant and i wondered why you told me you needed space and i agreed because i thought i needed it too but us being apart only made matters worse for me  i started over thinking things and found some things suspicious  i thought i couldn't live without you but i'm doing just fine my heart no longer melts to the sound of your laughter my stomach no longer flutters when i think of you my inner self no longer screams in happiness to the idea of seeing you i no longer smile to the sound of your name  it no longer kills me that we don't talk as much anymore my heart isn't broken anymore its just bruised i'm not disappointed anymore i'm not angry anymore i.  just.  don't.  care.  after a year and a few more months of pain and tears  i finally got a wake up call i don't need you with friends like mine,  who needs a boyfriend? you moved on and i realized that it was time i did the same

title: On

text: i'm running  i can't believe its so hard  my hearts pounding in my chest as i wonder if your right behind me  i hide under the sheets and act as if i am not here or anywhere then i turn around ,  i see u looking over me  i scream and pray you would just go away i kick  i'm running and running but you are still right there i've been running from you as long as i can remember  i stop running  i decide to face my fears just for the fact i wish to not run anymore as i look back you slowly start to get close close finally the last few steps  we are now face to face i see my eye my face my hair i see me then i realized i was just trying to get someone to open there eyes and see what i saw him doing  but its now to late   so much misery and pain has been cause its to late.  i try to wake up but its to late

title: I HATE YOU
author: chelsea
text: who am i ? ,  what do you really know bout me?! i'm an empty image, lost soul, broken heart , sometimes a waste of space.  you look up at me as i walk past,  but can't speak,  why?! i ask my self am i really that empty? is that why you hurt me more and more,  i often see your face so undecided   every time i look up at you i wish i could escape,  but these wall stay the same.   why do i see you night after night? i am  so afraid.  .  .  what i remember years ago.  you could see right through me ,  as i tried to hide  you haunt my sleep ,  i say i am over it but time doesn't heal everything,  i wish you could be gone from my head cause it hurts   i wish i could say so much to you and hurt as you i once hurt me then i remember  that some things are better said with the lights out & eyes closed.

title: WHY?

text: why does this always happen to me? does it ever happen to you? why does this always happen to me? do you know what i should do?  why does this always happen to me? do you know what i mean? why does this always happen to me? maybe itâ’s in my gene?  why does this always happen to me? maybe itâ’s a power coming from above? why does this always happen to me? maybe,  just maybe it's because of love!

'' the blue-eyed girl will build cigarette snow ash men and when she burned herself on a still lit ember,  the brown-eyed girl will suck her finger.  they are careful not to let the tree catch fire.  at night the little angel heals their wounds,  so in the morning they were bright-eyed,  ready to play again.

title: A Tear

title: That Room

text: braces how terrifying they seemed then in that room with the strangely comforting brownish-orange walls and the meaningless motivational posters protruding from the wall that when read,  fill you with   temporary,  flaming,  pure ambition to get something done but of course youâ’re stuck  in that room with the fluorescent lights directly above your eyes that you have to stare into  patterned with an army of hexagons lit from behind that look like faces staring right back  at you almost asleep in the soft,  impossibly comfortable  leather dentistâ’s chair next to the stand with the clean,  sterile,  gleaming tools of the trade forced to listen to the country mercilessly played through the speakers and,  of course that black speckled foam ceiling  a staple of every office building  that room and the doctorâ’s face,  his mouth moving behind his green surgeonâ’s mask telling you to turn your head to the left  that room so boring it detaches you from your cares,  your joys,  your sorrows your fears of not being able to chew gum how horrifying that prospect was (however detached you may be) and how lucky i was in that room

text: i am from telescopes from stars and moons i am from the clocks,  that strike 11:11 twice.  and the wishes we make that may or may not come true,  but we still do anyways  iâ’m from the late night talks and minimal sleep from the green eyes and soft brown hair iâ’m from the secrets and the hiding from the waiting that seems to never end the â“i love youâ”,   coming from the all too familiar faceless voice.   iâ’m from being taught love is not real from men that lie and cannot be trusted  but this is what i have learned isnâ’t true.  iâ’m from the love that is true from the men that prove others wrong.

title: Free For a Day
author: daisy
text: cold and no jacket.  no one to hold.  no one to love.  all alone.   not a soul in sight.  just the grass,  trees wind to comfort my emptiness.   the sound of my breath,  against the wind,  is all you hear.  along with the accents of rustling leaves in the trees that are so anxious to be free from their restraints  sometimes i wish kids could just be like falling leaves for a day kids could test their limits without judgement  be free from parents and rules do what makes them happy  just for a day,  maybe just maybe,  it would be good that way.

title: A poem for that special someone.
author: damion
text: another year passes; itâ’s the end of winter,  spring is coming; itâ’s inevitable; as the flowers start blooming,  thatâ’s when i spot her,  i begin walking towards her and almost stumble.   like an angel from heaven,  she dropped from the sky,  catching my arm,  and setting me upright; i look back up at her,  and caught the gaze of her eye,  the beauty of it fills my sight.   her eyes were like gemstones,  which none can compare,  a most beautiful blue,  around an orb,  as dark as deep space; both eyes were so charming,  i was content just to stare,  those pretty little gemstones were framed by the most beautiful face.   i felt unworthy of that hypnotic stare,  but she made not a move as she looked into my eyes; i thought her an apparition that would disappear in the air,  then she began to speak,  to my utter surprise.   her voice was so soothing,  music to my ears; her voice was so charming,  it brought me to tears.   but as all dreams must do,  it went up in a swirl; perhaps sometime soon,  i'll meet that special girl.

title: You're Gone
author: dana
text: it seems like yesterday,  i was holding you in my arms.  i promised to god i'd love you,  and keep you away from harm.  i suffered through the terrible two's,  as i held you close and kissed you goodnight,  sometimes you would get scared,  i would have to come in and turn on the light.  then you started school,  a chance for me to get away.  but then there were those days,  i wanted to hold you and make you stay.  i watched you get a little older,  i watched you run outside and play,  but in one split second,  my promise was stolen away.  i wasn't there to help you.  it's hard to realize your gone,  and that your flying with the angels.  your the sun that rises at dawn,  and the stars up in the heavens.  and yet i need to understand,  you walk with me everyday.  not just as a memory,  in my heart is where you stay.  but when i look back on those days,  and i almost start to cry.  i know you're in my heart,  this isn't our last goodbye.

title: Rain- the way we see it
author: divvya
text: with one last glance at those overcast skies,   i entered my house,  in a bad mood  for although the day went fine and school was fun,   the temperature outside was intolerable   all of us had high hopes looking at the weather last night  the trees swaying to the musical tune of the wind confirmed it downright  but then again,  today was the same old story; even the acâ’s were not soothing  i pulled the curtains aside and looked outside the window  but there was not even a drizzle,   in disappointment i glanced around and saw a lot of birds,   perched on many trees,  all chirping,  but not merrily,   they sounded like they were also anticipating  the moment when it would start raining  by now,  people had begun walking up and down their gardens,   not wanting to waste any more time,  i started closing the windows,    when suddenly i heard a sound which i had longed to hear since ages  a tiny rain drop landed with a soft plop on my elbow,    a smile lit up my face,  automatically    and i ran to my terrace and stood there,   letting the drops trickle down my body  it started raining more heavily and i was even happier  the more the merrier!  with one last glance at those crystal clear skies,   i rushed inside,  feeling content,   finally,  the hot weather goes  and rain comes.    - divvya

title: Morning
author: dorothy
text:
the sun whispers through the quiet house, its rays leaking through the window panes like water but everyone sleeps, ignoring the flood of light
that washes over them like the blankets in their beds.
the mother wakes first, and the current takes her downstairs
to start cooking breakfast. soon, the whole city is submerged
and the moon floats on the surface and dissapears into the waves,
not to appear again until low tide.

title: Hope
author: elizabeth
text: my mind unravels in the colors of incomplete thoughts and daydreams.      pages crumple and wither away in smeared ink,  bleeding out emotions left unexpressed.     uncertainty and doubt clouds my eyes as i waste in dry sobs,  going through the motions of trying to search for inspiration to fulfill what i never get to do anymore.      i wander in fields of never-ending twists and turns of constant repetition,  yearning to break free of the ties around my soul,  wanting to let go of the anchors,  but feeling too much anxiety to even attempt to do so.     because,  what would happen to me if i simply let go?   where would i drift off to and what would i have left to live for?  my mind struggles to climb atop the mountain of incomplete to-do lists,  nothing on the crumpled line paper scratched out,  feeling no accomplishments obtained.   my heart will thump to an irregular rhythm,  foreign to my body,  sweat clinging to my palms,  sending a shiver down my spine as the world around me fades into nothingness,  feeling like iâ’m trapped within my own unrealistic expectations.   what would happen if those expectations never existed?   would i actually be happier,  yet never being able to strive for something greater than myself?   but,  i find solace in my own values,  in my own faith; the very direction that has provided me with identity and reason since early childhood.     solely the single driving force that has given me the purpose to oppose the nagging voices of my own mind.     it is through the faith that i have grown up in that taught me of hope and that compassion can still exist within the eyes of the violent humanity that has become of us.      luminosity from the faith i follow overpowers the deathly waves that crash onto the crumbling shores of my mind every so often.      i then pick up a pencil,  allowing the graphite to glide across a clean sheet of paper,  reminding me that it's okay to start again.     repeating lines stroke back and forth,  shadowing smears across faces,  light gleaming in the eyes of people that i have never met across my paper.      lines of what i am too nervous to express are scrawled across sheets of paper in a tattered journal.     worn out covers protect my innermost thoughts,  collecting dust in between pages,  left behind and forgotten.     but the relief that i have felt will always be remembered.      lyrics and melodies fill my ears with what i cannot verbally express by myself.      tunes and words tell stories,  conveying ideas and dreams through the stringing together of self-expression,  reminding me of the advice that i fail to follow on my own.     pages filled with written and published words rip me away from a reality that i sometimes wish to abandon,  dragging me through worlds and creations that will never exist in this dimension.    my fingers intertwine with frayed shoelaces,  the soles of my feet pounding against pavement   mile after mile freeing me from where my heart beats to an irregular rhythm soon turning into a melodious beat of euphoria that i can only latch onto when iâ’m outside,  running against gravity itself.    i also find solace in the smiles and laughs that rest peacefully in my memories,  given by the people that i hold dear to my heart.     consoling words that they speak echo through my mind,  whispering to me that without the bad,  no one would know what the meaning of good is.      a phoenix cannot rise from the ashes if it never once disintegrated into a pile of embers.    happiness can always be found in reaching out to others who feel the same way; knowing that  iâ’ve never been the only one,  seeing that we all have the right to feel how we do.   knowing that i am blessed.    knowing that there is no such thing as being the only one in an infinite universe who feels a certain way.     i find solace in knowing that although the galaxies and the stars around us are ever-changing,  that although i am incredibly small in a world that never ceases to turn,  i am still filled with potential,  still my own being,  and still able to thrive.    i see it as a miracle.

title: Finding my way home
author: ellie
text: coming home from school,  i found indentions in the snow outlined from those before.  those recent and those from long ago.    my path to home,  always routine-- but now,  these footsteps,  --mesmerizing-- and with me,  did disagree.   footsteps filled with muck,  soot,  and dirt.  the snow no longer white.  scandal,  disgrace,  and shame filled their sad little plight.   a path drawn out for me.  i decided to follow,  stepping carefully.  to see where they could take a child such as me.   one in front of the other,  my feet began to fall.  to keep up with the footsteps thatâ’s path i did not recall.   unknowingly,  i strayed from the path that i knew would be best for me,  to travel my way to the place that i needed to be  dinner time was drawing near i sensed the setting of night.  the footsteps kept me going their way gave such invite.   footsteps led me through the darkness.  in a forest,  i was lost.  over a bridge and through the coldest of the wintry frost  footsteps of those who came before.  indented in the snow.  remain there forever.  because some can never let them go.   perhaps,  the snow will fall again covering up their path but mother nature remembers where these footsteps pasted.   i became scared and seemed to be alone.  until i found that these footsteps,  however misleading,  always led me home.   footsteps met the familiar road,  and helped me just the same.  allowed the lost and confused,  a trail of their own to claim.   home,  my home.  the indentions in the snow.  of those who came before  and those so long ago

text: as the sun goes down and my fans start to run i wonder why thereâ’s no longer  fun i look to my left and i see a family  the kids are playing and the mum calls out stanley i look to my right and i see something fading,  as if there was no point engraving engraving your memories into the sand as if i was a forgotten brand but my time has come and i bid thee farewell iâ’ll go back to my  past and wish in a well for a dream that seems so distant  i might never tell but whatâ’s the point in dreaming if your life isnâ’t swell? title: Girl
author: emma
text: i.  she inspects her three-sizes-too-big high-heeled feet,  clunking around in the muddy passageway.  a man strides past,   hurried bundled in his raggedy coat,  protecting from the uncertainty  of the moment and the sand whipping in the air.  he recollects his early days when there was security there was light. . .  splashing stomping  dancing,   the girl watches as her face ripples in the cloudy mirror.  she clasps her trench coat so as not to dirty  her clothes.  unkempt hair is kicked by the wind while  the young face buries itself into hunched shoulders.  stomping,  stomping,  trying to stomp away the horror and the crying.  oh! the crying! she kicks and kicks her rippling face,  trying to wake up.   ii.  meanwhile i am laughing my deep belly laugh at the parade.  small teeth glisten with traces of  lip gloss,  shaping a smile as wide as the great american flag.  a dripping cherry icee sits patiently in my lap,  the red straw,  poking into my chin,  impresses a small ''o'' into sun-kissed skin.  i clutch my rainbow change purse,  its interior pink plastic  and play currency.  my nostrils flare in delight as my belly laughs and i sit in the red radio flyer.  in blissful carelessness i think,  i am the happiest girl in the world.

text: people are everywhere,  cheering,  clapping their hands and shouting.  yep,  you guessed it,  barry bonds takes a stroll to the plate.   he steps in the box,  looks at the pitcher and  gets ready.   the pitcher looks in for the sign,  gets  it and sets up.   suddenly. . . all is silent.  everyone watches and waits,  waits,  waits.   waits for the big moment.   the pitcher winds up and throws.   everything stops.   slows down,  down like a snails pace.   cameras flash,  flash as the pitch heads toward home.  slow,  slow,  slow,  everything.   then. . .   crack!  everthing returns  to normal speed.   defening  sounds from the crowd's cheers and the ball goes flying.   back,  back,  back.  to the wall. . .  caught.   the ball is caught.  sorry barry,  you're  stuck at  659 for another day.

title: Somebody Else

title: My One and ONLY TRUE LOVE

text: love has many definitions, <br>but only one i can define:<br>the love that i went through<br>red as red as wine. <br>love is as pure as water<br>but it hurts as bad as thorns. <br>the love that i went through<br>till my heart was fatally torn. <br>pieces of my broken heart<br>fall upon the floor. <br>my tears stream down my cheeks<br>as i walk towards the door. <br>memories of our broken love<br>linger across my mind<br>i think of him every second of every day<br>true love i wish to find. <br>his walk,  his smile,  his eyes,  his mouth, <br>his talk,  his touch,  his height,  his health. <br>he's my all and my destiny, <br>he's my rock of love. <br>he helps me up when i'm feeling down. <br>it hurts to know that he doesn't love me back, <br>but it's good to know that we're just friends, <br>and that's a fact. <br>i now walk the many paths chosen by my thoughts, <br>for my faith is within me, <br>forever he'll be my destiny<br>i now know the true meaning of real love:<br>it's from me!!!

title: I Believe
author: felisha
text: i believe that god picked you out of all the rest because he knows that i love you best.  i have a heart that is warm and true now i would like to share it with you.  take care of it as i have done for a heart is not easily won,  and when i go to heaven and your not there i'll paint your face on the golden stairs so all the angels will know and see how you my darling mean to me,  so take care and beware go on your on way till we meet again on jugdement day.

title: Chaos and Strength
author: finn
text: chaos and strength    i am from chaos and strength,  from pieces of insanity and greatness.  i am from mountains that are taller than you think they are,  from cuts and bruises that may not heal.   i come from a disease that takes who you are,  and who you want to be.  i am from people who grow from their mistakes,  and come out stronger each time.  i am from a ragged piece of metal corroded by time,  of fighting the need to fight back the tears.  i am from dealing with a bomb with an unknown date to explode.  yet every bomb has a way to deactivate,  and my mom knew how.  you should never have to go through this alone.  so i may be from scars that will never heal,  and memories that arenâ’t all too great,  but i also come from someone who is strong and self controlled,  someone cares about how she affects other people.  i am from someone who has done everything for me  someone who i love.

title: Don't Turn Away from my Love
author: fiona
text: i've never told you this before but i guess i really showed how much you really mean to me and the things you never knew.   i used to hide the way i felt because i was so scared i thought you'd play my feelings by pretending that you cared.   the girls said you were up to something and i believed that this was true my heart gave up for a little while and i forgot about you.   i know i don't have a chance so why do i have to cry? i'm missing you so deeply that it's burning me inside.   you may have guessed who i am but please don't turn away because i need your words of strength to guide me everyday.   i know that if i lost you  my whole world would end so i'm just glad i know you if only as a friend.   you may not understand me but this i promise true-- from now on forever i will love and cherish you.

title: The Test
author: frankie
text: the tension is building my palms are wet,  i knew i should have studied harder.  i feel sick like a dog,  i need a vet,  man,  i am such a marder.   the clock is ticking i feel the stress,  i am doing the best that i can.  this eraser is making such a mess! could someone please turn on a fan?  only five minutes left and i am not even done,  i think i am about to cry.  i wish i could just get up and run,  oh well,  i gave it my best try.

title: 'Girls'
author: freddy
text: girls,  girls,  who are they? girls are so funny i think they are corny they need to see  the real world  it's turning and running from thoses girls  that are so corny  but not funny that's why i stop  to wonder who are they

title: Gates to the Promised Land
author: gabriela
text: you may have found the key to a free spirit in the promised land where everything is paradise.   and you may be cured of everything that has hit you full force in the past.   you may not be with us,  side by side,  taking a breath and letting it out.   but we hold you locked within each of our hearts.  and we carry you with us in remembrance.   you have been there through desparate times when the clouds drifted over our skies and rained through our eyes.   you have been there through times of smiles and joy as a set of teeth danced across each of our faces.   you were there for us all and still are even now as you reunite with the man you love.   we will never let you leave our hearts,  for the bars guarding them can never be opened.  you will remain in our thoughts forever,  for the memories we have shared are endless.   on this day,  a silent tear may fall,  but know that it is falling because we love you and we care.  it is falling because we know you have always been there.

title: Books
author: gabriela
text: oh how i could spend years reading books,   flipping through pages just to take a look.   i would see the words of brilliant writers,   scan every message and never get tired.   if i could one day own every novel,   that would be the farthest thing from awful!

title: Smile Today
author: gabriela
text: make sure to smile today,  spread your smile from ear to ear.  but there is one thing i must say,   you should have brushed your teeth,  oh dear!

title: Education
author: gabriela
text: it's sad that now every gets and education,   isn't it unfair even within our nation?  it is our duty to help others learn,   that even though it's ''just life'' they should also get a turn.   education helps even the blind to see,   that right and wrong are two separate things.   learning opens the hearts of the lonely,   and shows them that love is the only thing that is free.    education will solve the world's problems,   it is our duty today that we learn to solve them.

title: Dance Until Your Feet Turn Blue
author: gabriela
text: pump your fist to the rapid song,   don't worry,  don't worry you can't dance wrong,   stomp your feet 'til you rip your shoe,   dance until your feet turn blue.   waltz around until the music stops,    twist and turn until your partner drops,   tango 'til you catch the flu,  dance until your feet turn blue.

title: The Sun Rises
author: gabriela
text: the sun rises like a blooming flower,   it's rays shine through in our darkest hour,   in the midst of darkness our star will shine,   its warmth is his,  hers,  yours,  and mine.   beyond the hills the orange peeks through,   over the mountains where the roaring phoenix flew.   after the battles that took thousands of men,   our resilient sun will aways rise again.

title: Cats
author: gabriela
text: why do cats hate me so much?  why are cats always in a rush?  why are they always angry and hiss?  why am i someone they never miss?   maybe it's because god made them that way,   and maybe it's good that this way they will stay!

title: Cold
author: gabriela
text: we shiver in the cold,   with the sun behind us,   only each other we have to hold,   holding on tight without a fuss.

title: Pancakes
author: gabriela
text: there's nothing like pancakes eight,   syrup,  butter,  and fluff like a cake,   there's nothing like pancakes at noon,   blueberries and raspberries up the wazoo!  there's nothing like pancakes at dinner,   but you should stop there or you won't get thinner!

title: Stone
author: gabriela
text: i run my hands along the stone,   each word is inscribed.   the uneven surface bruises me,   the gray tones stay silent.

title: Texting and Driving
author: gabriela
text: we drive on the highway to go from here to there,   text and drive? how we dare!  keep your eyes up and on the road,   don't look down for your phone to load!

title: Wonderful
author: gabriela
text: how wonderful is this  life! the birds sing a new song,   while they eat baby frogs.   lions lick their paws,   but munch on innocent fawn.

title: Weddings
author: gabriela
text: wedding are the best don't you think?  the champagne glasses,  oh how they clink! dancing with the bride  and party with the groom,   spread joy and love until we can't see the moon.   weddings are fun and bring happiness,   to the bride and the groom,  and,  of course,  the rest!

title: Children
author: gabriela
text: children are lovely and care for all,   they pick you up when you trip and fall.   they love to play games and play in the rain,   oh how i wish my childhood remained!

title: Party
author: gabriela
text: drop your things and come to the party,   we'll have great food that's big and hearty!  blast the music so that we can't hear a sound,   even the voices of people around!

title: Equality
author: gabriela
text: why aren't we all equal? we are all born are we not?  we share the same soil and the same air,   yet we fail to make a world that's loving and fair.

title: Together
author: gabriela
text: together we must stand agains the tragedies of life,   locked hand in hand and always ready to love.   together is the only way we can bring ourselves to peace,   whether it be through treaties or covering our world with trees.

title: Cooking Competition
author: gabriela
text: i go to the international cooks competition and compete! the dish is magnificent! compared to cow manure.   why didn't i try this dish earlier?  then i wouldn't have qualified.   i did it! i achieved failure.

title: Teacher
author: gabriela
text: teachers guide us and protect us.   although not physically,   they show us the way to grow our minds.   teachers shape our very thoughts with their masterful hands,   and our broken thoughts they learn to mend.

title: Golf
author: gabriela
text: whoosh! the swing missed the ball! oh shoot! i try again.   one more time.   once again i swing,   yes! i hit it!  the ball lands in the water.

title: Roses
author: gabriela
text: roses blossom in the hard wind,  across deserted lands and flowing rivers.   in world of peace and war,   rose buds smile at the sun.

title: Past Days
author: gabriela
text: i remember past days,   when the wind carried away,   all the sadness of yesterday.

title: Sandwich
author: gabriela
text: my bread slices finally pop out of the toaster! burnt to a crisp.   picture-perfect lettuce sits safely in a bag.   pesticide caner.   ripe tomatoes squirt onto the cutting board.   mold on the inside.   i enjoy it anyways.   i'm allergic to sandwiches.

title: The Animal World
author: gabriela
text: in the forest all creatures roam,   under the earth's life-breathing dome,   birds and flies soar through the sky,   while penguins and chickens can only try.   tigers and pigs run across the land,   while crabs and oysters dig through the sand.

title: Hats
author: gabriela
text: every outfit needs a hat,   a tall one,  a round one,  or one that is fat! sombreros or buckets or baseball caps,   one's that tie or even snap!  so grab a hat at your local shop,   and maybe later we can swap!

title: Fight
author: gabriela
text: keep on fighting through the hail,   always push on and you will never fail,   don't let sadness get you down,   i promise everything will turn around.

title: Born
author: gabriela
text: we are born to help others in our lives,   feed and love those that are deprived,   give a hug or a helping hand,   unite together and take a stand.

title: Secrets
author: gabriela
text: we keep secrets that the world will never know,   the darkest facts that we'd never show,   but why don't we just open ourselves up? oh the things that would disrupt!

title: Laugh
author: gabriela
text: laugh today.   there is simply nothing like it.   nothing like those moments of pure happiness,   where nothing can ever go wrong.    but the return to reality is what keeps us from knowing,   the true influence of a good old laugh.

title: Goats
author: gabriela
text: today i saw a goat at the supermarket.  what a strange thing to say,   but even stranger to see.   it's rough face rummaged through the stacks of fresh muffins,   everyone just watched.

title: Anger
author: gabriela
text: anger is a terrible feeling,   it eats away at the soul,   leaving a dark stain of resentment and bitterness.    anger brings out the worst in everyone,   making a monster,   from our mistakes.

title: Red
author: gabriela
text: red is the color the world recognizes,   whether it came from the birth of a new life,   or the bloodshed of a worldwide crisis.   but red can be a happy color,  too.   it can be the color of your favorite food,   or the hue of your newest pair of shoes.   whether red is a color your recognize,   it's definitely a color that is the world's greatest prize.

title: Music
author: gabriela
text: you know how they say music guides the soul?  i can tell you know they were just being trolls.   music does so much more than lift your soul,   of your mind and body it gives you control.   the beat of a chorus heals broken hearts,   brings back together those that have been torn apart.   in a world with such devastation,   music is the true life behind all creation.   in the midst of chaos and despair,   a lovely tune can be the best repair.   music is the glue that holds us together,   yesterday,  tomorrow,  now,  and forever.

title: Be Glad You Are You
author: gabriela
text: be glad that your feet aren't on your head,   or you'll be walking upside down instead!   be glad that your nose isn't in your in your hand,   or you'll be smelling sweaty palms,  oh man!   be glad that your arms are not toes,   or you'll never be able to fight off your foes!   so be glad that you are you,   and nobody else,   because if you were,   i might not be myself!

title: A Whole New World
author: gabriela
text: a whole new world is what we all seek,   a place of safety for the strong and the meek,   a universe where everything is just,   and kindness to all is a definite must.   why don't we make our world this place?  a world of harmony for the human race.

title: Travel!
author: gabriela
text: one day in the future i would love to travel,   to see the world and all the things it will unravel,   to walk amongst many others to stand and see,   the landmarks of human history.   walk up a mountain,  just you and me,   to see the world where great men used to be.

title: Lost
author: gabrielle
text: i should have called.  why didn't i? that would have been our good bye.  now it's almost been 4 years,  i still think about how i promised i would call,  but i never did.  i never would have thought you would have gone so fast,  i'm so sorry.  the sorrow eats at me everyday.  i wish i could turn back the clock of life and called when i said i was going to.  how does it feel to be dead knowing you never have to die again? do you miss me,  do you miss us? can you talk or breath? how soon until i'm with you,  can you tell me that? i hope to see you soon,  your sorry,  great grand daughter

title: TRANSFORMATION
author: ganga
text: when i was in first   my mother ,  hugged me and kissed me     and said ;  'take care my baby '  when i was in forth ,  she hold my little hand   in her palm   and said; 'take care my child'  when i was in tenth,    she embraced me     and said; 'take care my girl'  when i was eighteen ,  she patted me on my shoulder       and said; 'take care my young lady '  when i got a job,  i patted on her shoulder     and told her,  ''take care yourself''

title: On my head
author: gareth
text: when i awoke one morning,   a stork was on my head.  i asked,  ''what are you doing there?''  it looked at me and said  why are you staring at me like you have seen a gohst.  that's no reason to stare.  now will you stop it please

title: Cards
author: garrett
text: i open the tattered red package and begin a trip back through time.  i can feel the soft carpet,   rubbing between my bare toes.  the room is hot and the scent of grandmaâ’s frosted cinnamon rolls linger in the air.  i slide the faded red cards out of the deck.   the edges are rough like my grandfatherâ’s hands of labor,   worn by many years of use.  the faces of the cards are old and soft  and slide through my hands like butter.  they have seen many years and many games,  both good and bad.  i can still see my grandfather that day,   and i can still hear the soft frailty in his voice.  they were his lucky cards,  his lucky cards for fifteen years.   and he was giving them to me.  he swore they would serve me well for many years,  and in a way they have.  they serve as a connection between my grandfather and i.  i may never see him again,   but as long as i have his cards,  he will never be far from me.

title: Dusshera
author: gayatri
text: as we go all the way around we see dusshera as we surround dusshera is a day of joy when all of us enjoy  then lord ram that day gave all of us a cause for celebration  this is a day when all the  evil light died  i love diwali a festival of crackers when we all wear new cloths and exchange sweets.

title: Happiness
author: grace
text: as a ray of light,  shattering the night,  \tlike a glorious sound,  bringing joy and peace  \tto all who hear,  happiness spreads light,  \treaching others with contagious increase  \tof delight,  illuminating oneâ’s heart \twith bliss and contentment.   glistening eyes \tand smiles illustrate many fine arts.  \tperfect reflection,  like clear bright blue skies,  \tof oneâ’s soul.  happiness: the breath of life \ta gift from god above,  given to me.  \tthis offering freely given ends strife \twith blessings no one can foresee.  \tbut true happiness,  worth much more than gold,  \tfor jesus,  his love he did not withhold.

title: Upon the Hill
author: grace
text: \ti strode along at the start of may,  \tthe songbirds singing while the crickets play,  \tand in early morning,  the sun had yet to chase the chill \ti stumbled upon a small,  yet foreboding hill.   as i gazed upon the hill,   \ti spied a house,  along and still,  \tand with much effort,  for the path was hard \ti reached the house and its front yard.   \tthough little grew upon this mount,  \tthe yard overflowed with flowers,  more than i could count.  \tand all well kept,  these colors created,  \ta masterpiece,  a picture unrestrained.    \tthen,  as if by chance,  the owner looked out,  \tand saw me standing there,  upon his mount.  \twith a cheery word and a kindly wave,  \the invited me inside his cozy cave.   \this eyes looked loving as they sparkled and gleamed,  \this smile,  perfect,  or at lease to me it seemed.  \tthe gracious air he had put me at ease,  \this manner and style was a gentle,  refreshing breeze.   \tafter tea and bread and cake,  \twe talked and laughed,  contented,  no mistake.  \tthe time flew by,  and all too soon,  \ttime came for me to head home,  at half past noon.   \ti still remember him,  standing in the gate,  slightly bent.  \twatching me make my descent.  \tand i ponder with a smile still \thow i had found a friend upon that hill.

title: A  Rose In Winter
author: guinevere
text: a rose in winter,  in the freezing cold night,  such a pretty sight to see.  alas how long will it last? for it to be is a mystery to me.  a rose in winter,  bright colors to the white snow,  sleighs and bells and all that's well.  there is a rose in the winter.

title: The System of Stars.
author: hailey
text: you were a solar system,  that i desired to know.   dark,  a mystery waiting to be unwound.  your eyes were constellations,  that i traced on my paper to remember how you looked at me.  your hands were meteors and moons,  molded by the stones that hit them.   your lips were shooting stars,  for i wished everyday to kiss them.  your works were the darkness of the sky.  vast.  empty.  cold.  yet beautiful.  and you were the sun,  seeming so warm,  so inviting,  so kind.  until i got too close and you burned me.  so i could not feel anymore.  you were a solar system,  and i was exploring.

title: My favrit sein is otover
author: hailey
text: sum times it is cold aot sied and sum tims the sun is aot sied and the leafs are green and red and a lot uv clolrs  and thar is sunset aot siyd thas it

title: My cats
author: haley
text: my cats are like soft pebbles in a midnight stream.  one is a yellowish-brownish-black with a sweet greenish-yellowish-blue glare.      the other signals night herself.  eyes like stars.  whiskers like needles.  with a yellow stare to add.      they leap to the moon on powerful legs.  detect dangers with large pointed ears.  but last of all a heart full  of love left for me.

title: *For Now
author: haley
text: people stair,  i think of what i did,  and begin to feel heart broken,  people talk,  im torn,  people call me fake,  a snitch,  a lier,  i feel lost,  and out of breath,  get me out,  im done,  im gone,  for now.

title: Me
author: halie
text: my eyes are blue,  my hair is blonde,  i'm always bright and merry.  i look like carrie underwood.  i like to sing and draw.  i like to song my favorite songs.  my vocie is like an angel's song.  i, m very,  very talented.

title: Smokey
author: halie
text: hogging the pillows late at night.  gaurding the house all through the day.  loving,  careing that is he,  never straying away from me.  black and white and full of life,  with eyes that glow like gems.  fur as soft as cotton,  yet heavy as a basket of clothes.  that is smokey.

title: Sunny
author: hallie
text: long bay legs stretch across the dry thumping dirt.  black tangled main blowing up and down in the cool breeze smooth  soft skin rubbing your legs never felt more free than when riding sunny  bare bake in the wind across the pasture

title: Lifeline!!
author: hanisha
text: my story runs three years back, as i met a girl with stupidness a whole full sack.  her role in my life is too versatile,  unaware of sadness,  she beautifully smiles.  there's a bond that we cherish,  many more years and decades to flourish.  brings me smiles everyday,  sometimes she's a headache all the way.  artistically is the way she paints,  a bank where all my secrets acquaint.  best friend but only mine,  god has blessed with a lifeline. . . !!

title: Winter Mornings
author: hanna
text: looking out the window i see snow slowly trickle down like it's a race for last place the flakes being pushed by the breeze until it gently lays on the snow covered surface i see the snowman standing on our lawn his carrot nose coated in white fluff and his scarf waving as the wind picks up i see the snowmobile drive by throwing snow aside like a leaf blower in fall creating a path ahead and leaving a trail behind i smell the fire glowing downstairs and hear the crackle of the timbers but now i have to leave slowly,  my joy simmers

title: Theres a bone in a tree!!!
author: hannah
text: theres a bone in a tree and a road on a rat theres a hog wearing togs and some bats wearing hats theres a bed on me  and a maths book on my head theres a moth in my moose  and thats whats i said!!
